research/history_archive/10_20260321_011318/session_brief.json:4:  "current_focus": "Treat K=128 only as the initial search anchor, not as a success criterion. The research objective is to find configurations whose FVU is dramatically better than the current K=128 baseline, with a target on the order of halving that baseline FVU before rewarding smaller K or lower cost.",
research/history_archive/10_20260321_011318/session_brief.json:70:      "hypothesis": "A gated SAE with a separate support-selection encoder can reduce support interference versus plain TopK at K=128, improving FVU before spending effort on smaller-K or cost optimizations.",
research/history_archive/10_20260321_011318/session_brief.json:130:        "If gated is quality-neutral but slower, separate implementation cost from architectural value before discarding it.",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0008.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"hybrid_topk has now beaten the K=128 full baseline, so the next quality-first move is to stabilize the same family with an optimizer better suited to its smooth nonlinear residual branch. Test hybrid_topk at K=128 with Adam to see whether denser adaptive updates improve FVU beyond the current full frontier.","summary":"hybrid_topk is the first family to improve the K=128 full frontier, but the gain is still small relative to the aggressive quality target. This round keeps the architecture fixed and changes only the optimizer to probe whether the family is currently undertrained rather than intrinsically capped.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a disciplined follow-up because the family finally showed real full-run promise and deserves one quality-focused stabilization pass before opening more architectures. Adam may not help, but it tests a concrete training-dynamics hypothesis without confounding the model design.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["hybrid_topk is now the best full K=128 frontier at FVU 0.18129383772611618, narrowly beating the previous topk anchor 0.18532327562570572.","Round 8 keeps focus on hybrid_topk and tests whether Adam can better optimize its nonlinear residual branch than signum."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk plus Adam improves proxy FVU, promote it to full as the new mainline family candidate.","If hybrid_topk plus Adam is flat or worse, keep the family but try a higher-capacity quality pass such as larger expansion_factor before considering cost reduction or lower K."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0005.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"factorized_topk likely failed because its hidden mixer is too narrow and lossy; widening that stage and adding a gate should preserve more information before latent selection and materially improve FVU. Re-test factorized_topk at K=128 after this single architectural stabilization edit.","summary":"The first factorized_topk prototype was much worse than the anchor, but its implementation used a plain hidden layer with width equal to d_in, which is a likely bottleneck rather than a decisive family verdict. This round keeps the same family and K while upgrading the encoder to a wider gated mixer.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a coherent follow-up on the only family that produced a strongly different signal, and it targets an obvious implementation bottleneck instead of abandoning the branch too early. The edit increases encoder compute, so even a quality gain still needs later cost scrutiny.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The original factorized_topk prototype likely suffered from an overly narrow d_in-sized hidden bottleneck rather than only a bad family prior.","Round 5 stabilizes factorized_topk by replacing the narrow ReLU mixer with a wider gated hidden stage before latent projection."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stabilized factorized_topk proxy improves substantially, consider promotion or a follow-up quality pass with optimizer tuning.","If the stabilized factorized_topk remains poor under normal runtime, deprioritize the current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder family rather than more local tuning."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0007.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A hybrid encoder that preserves the strong linear topk path and adds a gated nonlinear residual to latent logits can improve quality without discarding the baseline behavior that already works. Test a new hybrid_topk family at K=128 as a quality-first architecture probe.","summary":"factorized_topk improved from its worst prototype but is still far from the K=128 anchor, and the current built-in families are not showing a path to the target. This round opens a new family designed to be safer than pure nonlinear encoders by keeping the baseline linear path intact and only learning a nonlinear correction on top.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a broader architecture move, but it is still a single coherent bet: combine the proven linear encoder with a nonlinear residual branch instead of replacing it. The new family adds compute, so even a promising quality signal would need later cost validation.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/hybrid_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The fixed factorized_topk stabilization improved proxy FVU from 0.4431915953755379 to 0.3485000617802143 without runtime regression, but it remains far from the K=128 topk anchor.","Round 7 opens hybrid_topk, a new family that keeps the baseline linear topk encoder and adds a gated nonlinear residual to latent logits rather than replacing the linear path outright."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk shows a clear proxy gain, follow with a stabilization pass on optimizer or nonlinear branch width before promotion.","If hybrid_topk is also flat or worse, pause family proliferation and reconsider whether quality gains are more likely to come from topk-mainline training dynamics than from encoder architecture alone."]}
