research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/results.tsv:15:proxy_1774006087	1774006087	proxy	ok	discard	0.27785650826990604	128	hybrid_topk	8			5013504	/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0010_proxy/round0010_proxy_1774006026_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef8_k128_20260320_192713	d4fe4e171c6a0a1fc12b7b89509cb054f764149d	autoresearch-sae	True	The expansion_factor=16 follow-up did not improve full FVU and cost substantial throughput, so the next move should be a targeted architecture refinement rather than more brute-force scaling. This round keeps the winning hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 setup and upgrades the nonlinear branch to modulate linear logits as well as add residual logits.	This is a narrow, defensible follow-up on the current best family and it directly addresses the likely limit of the present hybrid design without reopening the broader search space. It still adds encoder complexity, so any quality gain will need later cost scrutiny against the ef=8 Adam mainline.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/proxy_1774006087.log
