research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/results.tsv:4:proxy_1774027698	1774027698	proxy	ok	discard	0.3432992845773697	128	jumprelu	8			5013504	/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0003_proxy/round0003_proxy_1774027397_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef8_k128_20260321_012324	a744ec309db0710ac0c3421b354e5cd34b931569	autoresearch-sae	True	Advance the `jumprelu` family from prototype to stabilization with a single family-specific parameter sweep point at the K=128 anchor. Keep architecture and optimizer fixed and test a sharper thresholded encoder to see whether the current 0.1888 full FVU can be pushed materially lower before considering any cost tradeoffs.	This is a focused follow-up on the only family with positive evidence so far. The main risk is over-sparsifying early and hurting reconstruction, but that is the right failure mode to test next because the current signal suggests threshold behavior is the key family-specific lever.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/proxy_1774027698.log
