research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 49 answered the `K=16` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=16` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally fails under extreme support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `8`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best ultra-low-cost point, or does the family advantage break once support becomes very tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `16` to `8` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=8` control (`0.380332`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the ultra-low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=16` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, `K=24`, and `K=16`. The main risk is that `K=8` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=16`: it beat the previous `K=16` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 50 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=8`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens sharply."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@8` clearly beats the existing `K=8` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=4` under the same recipe to locate the final break point.","If `gated@8` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=16` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
