research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 48 answered the `K=24` question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) continued to transfer downward and now owns the `K=24` frontier with a materially better endpoint than the prior control. The next single question is where this benefit finally breaks under stronger support pressure: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `16`, does `gated` still preserve enough quality to remain the best low-cost point, or does the family advantage disappear once support becomes this tight?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the recent K sweep has now shown successful transfer at `K=96`, `K=64`, `K=32`, and `K=24`. The main risk is that `K=16` may fall outside the regime where the improved gating recipe remains effective, but that is exactly the highest-value remaining single-variable question for locating the LUTurbo cost-quality break point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers down to `K=24`: it beat the previous `K=24` control and now holds that frontier point.","Round 49 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether the same recipe still wins at `K=16`, where LUTurbo online cost drops further but support pressure tightens again."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@16` clearly beats the existing `K=16` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=8` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@16` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=24` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0209.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单样本 top-k 选择后的单库查表与加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。r208 已证明 topk 在 EF=1、K=64、total_cost=0.31x 下能显著优于此前 factorized_topk 低开销点，因此本轮保持 architecture=topk、EXPANSION_FACTOR=1、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 K 从 64 提到 96，沿 deployment 成本轴在 <0.5x 区域内换取更低 FVU。预计 deployment cost 由约 0.06x 升到约 0.09x，total_cost 约为 0.34x，仍稳居低开销区，同时有望明显改善当前 0.2583 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=96 在 EF=1 下明显改善 FVU 且仍保持较快训练吞吐，可继续单变量上探 K=128，寻找 <0.5x 内的更优 topk 前沿点。","如果 K=96 改善有限，则说明 EF=1 的字典容量已成为主瓶颈，下一步应转向新的低成本 family，而不是继续在 topk@EF1 上增加查表预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk@EF1 已经证明比同成本附近的 factorized_topk 更强，当前优先级应是在该 family 内补足 <0.5x 区域的 K 轴形状。","本轮只改 K，保持 encoder 成本不变，便于将收益或退化归因于 lookup 预算变化。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，并直接面向 <0.5x 区域补点。主要风险是 K 增加带来训练时间上升，但相较于可能获得的 FVU 改善，这一代价在当前阶段可接受，且仍需结合 tokens_per_sec 一并评估。","summary":"固定 topk 的 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只将 K 从 64 提升到 96，目标是在约 0.34x 总成本处获得一个比当前 0.31x 点更低 FVU 的新低开销 Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0005.json:52:    "self_review": "This is a coherent follow-up on the only family that produced a strongly different signal, and it targets an obvious implementation bottleneck instead of abandoning the branch too early. The edit increases encoder compute, so even a quality gain still needs later cost scrutiny.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0139.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"STAGE1_RATIO","value":"0.75"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束；本轮只改两阶段预算分配，不改变 family、EF、K、optimizer、LR，也不改变最终导出形式。r138 表明把 LR 下调到 2.4e-3 会在相同吞吐和相同总 token 下把整条曲线都拉差，说明“LR 偏大”假设已基本排除；而 `adam` 在该可行主线上已有明确负信号，AUXK/TRUNK_RANK/NUM_CODES 近几轮也未给出新增益。当前尚未被回答的单一问题是：在相同总 K=128 下，将两阶段预算从默认近似 50/50 改为更前置的 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75，是否能让第一阶段承担更多粗重构，从而改善低 EF regime 的中后段收敛并把 FVU 压回 0.0581 以下。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 改善终点 FVU 或曲线中后段形状，则继续在同 family 上围绕 stage budget 做更细的单变量搜索。","若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 明显变差，则说明低 EF 主线不受益于前置预算，后续可反向测试更保守的 STAGE1_RATIO=0.25 或关闭该轴。","若 STAGE1_RATIO=0.75 与 baseline 几乎等价，则说明两阶段预算分配不是当前瓶颈，后续应回到更贴近 deploy 成本的已知轴而非继续做 recipe 微调。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的导出形式未变，仍属扩展兼容，可继续作为 LUTurbo 主线 family。","r138 在相同 tokens_per_sec 与 final_total_tokens 下整条曲线变差，基本排除了“把 signum LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3 会改善收敛”的假设。","在 optimizer 与常见 loss 轴都缺乏正信号后，STAGE1_RATIO 是当前仍未回答、且不改变导出契约的两阶段内部预算问题。"],"primary_variable":"stage1_ratio","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 STAGE1_RATIO，family、EF、K、optimizer、LR 保持当前主线参考配方不变。该动作保持 LUTurbo 导出契约不变，且不应触碰 encoder 选择成本硬约束；风险是 75/25 过于激进，可能重演历史上非对称预算的负信号，因此评估时必须同时看完整曲线、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最终 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 family，不开新架构；在 clean baseline 与 LR 下降试验之后，转向尚未回答的两阶段内部预算问题：保持 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 STAGE1_RATIO 设为 0.75，测试更前置的 stage1 预算能否在不增加在线成本的前提下改善低 EF 主线的收敛与 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0013.json:51:    "self_review": "This is a single coherent family exploration, not another weak local sweep. The main risk is that sigmoid-gated selection could saturate and undertrain, but the architectural change is clean, already implemented, and directly targets support quality rather than cost.",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0013.json:77:      "If gated shows a strong proxy signal, promote it to full before returning to smaller-K or cost work.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0211.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"reduce_total_cost_into_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 u_r 是 trunk 静态向量库，b_i 是 residual 静态向量库；部署到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时可拆成 trunk 库查表加权和与 residual 库查表加权和，两部分都是静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此属于扩展兼容。r210 在 K=64、EF=1 下给出 0.69x / 0.1256，说明该 family 的质量明显优于 topk，但当前瓶颈是 trunk 带来的额外成本而非训练失稳。本轮保持 architecture、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只将 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 16，目标是同时压低 encoder 与 deployment 两侧的 trunk 成本，把 total_cost 尽量拉回 <0.5x 区域，同时保留一部分 low-rank coarse 表达能力。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 能把 lowrank_factorized_residual 拉进 <0.5x 且 FVU 仍明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则继续固定该 family，单变量扫描 K 或更小的 TRUNK_RANK 以补齐低开销前沿。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 仍无法进入 <0.5x 或 FVU 明显崩塌，则说明该 family 在低开销区的 trunk 分支仍然过重，下一步应回到更短链路 family，而不是继续沿 lowrank 分支推进。"],"notes_to_memory":["r210 证明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低 EF 下具备高质量潜力，但 0.69x 的主要问题是成本而非效果。","TRUNK_RANK 是该 family 最直接的降本旋钮，且同时作用于 encoder 和 deployment，比继续调 K 更符合本轮把点拉回 <0.5x 的目标。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"该提案严格只改一个主变量，并直接针对 r210 暴露的主要矛盾：质量足够好但成本偏高。风险是 rank=16 可能过于激进导致 FVU 回退，但这是判断 lowrank family 能否进入低开销区所必需的高信息量实验。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，仅将 TRUNK_RANK 设为 16，测试能否通过压缩 trunk 成本，把 0.69x/0.1256 这条高质量边界点推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0007.json:79:    "self_review": "This is a broader architecture move, but it is still a single coherent bet: combine the proven linear encoder with a nonlinear residual branch instead of replacing it. The new family adds compute, so even a promising quality signal would need later cost validation.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0215.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"192"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此兼容性为直接兼容。r214 已证明在 EF=1 下把 K 从 64 提到 128 能把 <0.5x 区域的 FVU 从 0.2583 压到 0.1968，说明当前低开销区的主瓶颈更像是查表预算不足，而不是 topk family 已经到头；因此本轮继续沿同一最短链路 family 提升 K 到 192，目标是在总成本仍预计约 0.43x、明显低于 0.5x 的条件下，进一步压低低开销区最佳 FVU，验证 topk@EF1 是否还能继续向可用前沿逼近。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@EF1,K192 在 <0.5x 内继续明显改善 FVU 且吞吐下降可接受，则同 family 的低开销前沿可继续沿 K 轴补一个更细点。","如果 K192 的收益很小但训练时间或 tokens_per_sec 明显变差，则说明 EF=1 下继续堆 K 的边际收益开始耗尽，后续应转向新的低成本 family 而不是再加查表预算。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是当前唯一已在 <0.5x 区域稳定形成两个可行点的直接兼容 family，且导出路径最简单，适合作为低开销主线基准。","r214 已经给出明确正信号：在 EF=1 保持 encoder 成本不变时，增加 K 能显著改善 FVU，因此当前最有信息量的单变量仍是 K 轴。","评估时必须同步检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，确认新增查表预算是否值得。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮延续已验证有效的低开销 topk 主线，不再重复被 policy 卡住的 lowrank_factorized_residual param_only 路线。选择 K=192 而不是先补 K=96，是因为当前任务优先级是尽快把 <0.5x 区域的最佳 FVU 压低，而不是细化已明显被 K=128 支配的中间点；风险是更高 K 可能带来吞吐下降和更长总耗时。","summary":"继续使用直接兼容的 topk family，固定 EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，把 K 提到 192，测试是否能在仍低于 0.5x 总成本的前提下，把低开销区最佳 FVU 从 0.1968 进一步压低。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 21 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=96` is a promising high-quality reduced-cost point: its curve kept descending smoothly through the late phase, and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` stayed very low. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis, lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping the `K=96` recipe fixed, to answer whether the new near-anchor deployment point is slightly over-regularized and can recover a bit more reconstruction quality without destabilizing training.","summary":"Run a single loss-axis test on the newly validated `K=96` topk point: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=96`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves the high-quality reduced-cost recipe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`other_param` via `AUXK_ALPHA`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed `K=96` curve shape. The main risk is that the gain may be small, but `K=96` is now the most promising reduced-cost point and its very low dead-feature pressure makes a clean over-regularization check more justified than continuing to remap K.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 21 established `K=96` as a strong high-quality reduced-cost point: late-phase FVU kept descending smoothly and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` remained near zero.","Because `K=96` is not capacity-stressed like the low-K regime, it is a better place than `K=8` or `K=16` to test whether the current auxiliary dead-feature pressure is slightly too strong.","This round returns from K mapping to recipe tuning, while still staying inside the same family and on a deployment-relevant point rather than retreating all the way to the K128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves `K=96`, keep the same K fixed and continue recipe refinement there before revisiting other K values.","If lower `AUXK_ALPHA` does not help, treat the current `K=96/signum/LR=1.6e-3` recipe as close to saturated and move to another single recipe axis.","If reducing `AUXK_ALPHA` hurts stability or quality, the current auxiliary pressure is likely already appropriate for this near-anchor reduced-cost point."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0164.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual with K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 unchanged. Final reconstruction remains x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j, where U(Vx) is a static low-rank trunk library, {c_m} is a static codebook library, and {b_i} is a static residual dictionary; only the stage-1/stage-2 budget split changes to a front-loaded 75/25 allocation. This is 扩展兼容 and exports cleanly to LUTurbo as trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two residual sparse lookups. Because this variant reuses the parent encoder modules, its selection-cost profile should stay matched to the mainline EF=2 point instead of introducing extra router/bucket scorer cost; the probe asks whether front-loading support budget improves low-EF reconstruction enough to justify future tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If this probe is clearly worse in FVU or runtime, return directly to the mainline lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual recipe next round.","If it is competitive at similar runtime, the next single-variable follow-up is STAGE1_RATIO tuning within this asymmetric family rather than opening another new architecture family."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: 扩展兼容. Export formula: x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j.","Probe choice rationale: matched to the current mainline formula class and likely budget-safe at EF=2, unlike routed/bucketed matched probes which add extra selector layers and risk policy rejection on selection cost.","This round is intentionally only an architecture probe; K=128, EF=2, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=3.0e-3 stay fixed."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Upside is bounded because this family only changes a fixed stage split and was not strong historically at higher-EF regimes, so a null result is plausible. Still, it is the cleanest policy-safe matched probe that isolates architecture without confounding cost increases.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe with ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual and keep the mainline recipe otherwise unchanged. It preserves LUTurbo-exportable static-library reconstruction and mainline-like selection cost, so the result will answer whether asymmetric budget allocation is worth any continued attention in the current low-EF regime.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0008.json:104:      "If hybrid_topk plus Adam is flat or worse, keep the family but try a higher-capacity quality pass such as larger expansion_factor before considering cost reduction or lower K."
research/history_archive/history_20260320_152535/logs/agent_action_0007.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current residual_topk prototype is likely capped by its fixed half-and-half latent budget: each branch can only nominate roughly K/2 features before the final merge, so the better branch cannot claim more of the final support even when it should. Letting both branches over-propose up to K candidates and then selecting the final global top-K from their union should preserve the residual design while removing this allocation bottleneck, improving FVU at fixed K=128.","summary":"Stabilize the promoted residual_topk family with a narrow architecture edit: remove the fixed per-branch K split so both the base and residual branches can each propose up to K candidates before the final global top-K selection. Run this as a proxy quality-first comparison at K=128 with the existing Hadamard+signum setup to test whether the family had been artificially capacity-limited.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within one coherent hypothesis and follows the program guidance to keep pushing a promising family before chasing smaller K or cost. I kept the execution layer unchanged, edited only sparsify/, and avoided mixing in optimizer or regularization sweeps so the result isolates the branch-allocation change. The main risk is extra duplicate candidates across branches with no quality gain, but the local forward/backward sanity check passed and runtime cost should remain close enough for a proxy read.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/residual_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Read research/program.md before deciding and respected the quality-first objective; with residual_topk newly promoted and still far from the aggressive target, a family-specific stabilization edit is more justified than smaller-K search.","No operator_hints were present in the structured context for this round.","Updated residual_topk so both branches can each propose up to K candidates before the final global top-k, removing the previous fixed half-and-half branch budget that could cap the family.","Local sanity check passed after the edit: residual_topk still instantiates and runs forward/backward successfully on a toy tensor."],"next_hypotheses":["If oversubscribed residual_topk improves proxy FVU, promote to full and then test residual_topk-specific stabilization such as ortho_lambda or Adam without changing K.","If quality improves but throughput regresses, follow with an edit_perf_code pass focused on the residual branch merge path rather than discarding the family.","If this edit does not improve residual_topk meaningfully, move to a different higher-expressivity family such as a factorized or wider multi-branch routed encoder instead of continuing narrow local sweeps."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/timeline.jsonl:129:{"event_id": "evt_1774005272724533136", "ts": 1774005272, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 9, "session_id": "019d0ad1-3a24-7583-a982-5e5d5ddd449d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "hybrid_topk", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0ad1-3a24-7583-a982-5e5d5ddd449d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "hybrid_topk", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "hybrid_topk with Adam is now the strongest K=128 configuration, so the next quality-first move is to increase representational capacity rather than shrink K or chase cost. Test hybrid_topk at K=128 with Adam and expansion_factor=16 to see whether extra latent capacity can materially reduce FVU again."}}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0250.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"On the directly compatible `topk` line, increasing `K` from 96 to 160 should produce a materially better `<0.5x` Pareto point, likely around the low-0.18 FVU range at about 0.41x total_cost, while avoiding the recent `factorized_topk` pattern of modest quality gains paired with worse throughput.","summary":"Use `topk` as the next low-cost mainline probe, anchored to r242 and changing only `K` to 160. Final reconstruction formula remains `x_hat = Σ_{i in TopK(x)} α_i(x) b_i`, where all `b_i` come from one static vector library, so this family is `直接兼容` with the LUTurbo/Lottable `查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿` path. This is a strict single-variable step inside the target `<0.5x` region: estimated selection cost stays at the EF=1 topk baseline, deployment lookup rises with `K`, and combined cost should land near 0.41x, filling the gap between the existing 0.38x/0.1968 and 0.44x/0.1635 topk points. Recent `factorized_topk` rounds improved FVU only slightly while increasing runtime cost, so the cleaner frontier-building move is to continue the already monotone-improving topk K ladder.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is intentionally conservative: it does not open a new family, and it relies on the existing topk trend rather than a new mechanism. The tradeoff is that it will not teach much about new structure, but that is acceptable here because the current priority is to strengthen the `<0.5x` Pareto frontier with a deployable, directly compatible point and to avoid recipes that slow training without a commensurate FVU gain.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"160"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Recent `factorized_topk` rounds remained far above the best low-cost topk points, and the wider scorer pass at r249 also reduced throughput to about 111k tok/s, so further factorized widening is currently a weak cost-quality bet.","The EF=1 `topk` K ladder has shown consistent FVU improvement from K=96 to K=128 to K=192 without any compatibility risk; an untested midpoint K=160 is the cleanest next `<0.5x` frontier probe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `topk` K=160 lands near the expected ~0.18 FVU at ~0.41x, test `K=176` next to refine the mid-right edge of the `<0.5x` frontier.","If `topk` K=160 underperforms the monotone trend, shift the next round to a different directly compatible low-cost selector family instead of continuing dense K sweeps.","If runtime regresses disproportionately at K=160, treat that as a system-side warning and prefer lower-cost frontier densification over larger-K topk pushes."],"reference_round":242}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0010.json:47:    "summary": "The expansion_factor=16 follow-up did not improve full FVU and cost substantial throughput, so the next move should be a targeted architecture refinement rather than more brute-force scaling. This round keeps the winning hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 setup and upgrades the nonlinear branch to modulate linear logits as well as add residual logits.",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0010.json:53:    "self_review": "This is a narrow, defensible follow-up on the current best family and it directly addresses the likely limit of the present hybrid design without reopening the broader search space. It still adds encoder complexity, so any quality gain will need later cost scrutiny against the ef=8 Adam mainline.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0154.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.3e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r153 已用 clean baseline 重新确认主线参考配方在当前运行环境下能稳定回到 FVU≈0.058106 且总耗时降回 294s，说明近期慢速样本更像吞吐波动而非 family 退化；因此本轮只回答一个问题：在主线 family、K、EF、optimizer 与导出形式不变的前提下，把 LR 从 3.0e-3 上调到此前两次出现更低终点的 3.3e-3，能否在正常吞吐区间内稳定复现更好的中后段收敛与更低 FVU，而不是仅仅依赖异常慢速运行。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 3.3e-3 在接近 r153 的 tokens_per_sec/总耗时下再次稳定优于 3.0e-3，则把 3.3e-3 升格为该 family 的 signum 主线 LR。","若 3.3e-3 回落到接近 3.0e-3，或只有在明显更慢时才略优，则关闭 LR 上调分支，保留 3.0e-3 作为更稳的主线锚点。","若 3.3e-3 终点更好但曲线出现更早震荡或平台，则不再继续上探 LR，后续只在已确认较优的 LR 上考虑 optimizer 或更贴近系统成本的单变量轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性仍为扩展兼容。","EF=2 继续满足选择成本预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 LR 轴混杂。","r153 clean baseline 恢复到 294s，说明近期 391s/453s 更可能是吞吐异常而非训练更长。","评估本轮时必须同时记录 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时、final_total_tokens，判断 3.3e-3 的收益是否独立于运行时慢速样本。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。按照推荐顺序，EF 已确认在预算内，clean baseline 已补齐，现在进入学习率轴是最小且可归因的下一步。","summary":"继续围绕主线 family 推进，不开新 family；在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 固定的前提下，仅把 LR 从 3.0e-3 调到 3.3e-3，验证此前的小幅 FVU 改善能否在正常运行代价下稳定复现。","touched_files":[]}
