research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/results.tsv:251:r250_1774702664	1774702664	ok	keep	0.1773166060447693	160	topk	1				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0250/round0250_standard_1774702476_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef1_k160_20260328_205442	16131257bc58ac32b94f751ef359e85ea46627a9			Use `topk` as the next low-cost mainline probe, anchored to r242 and changing only `K` to 160. Final reconstruction formula remains `x_hat = Σ_{i in TopK(x)} α_i(x) b_i`, where all `b_i` come from one static vector library, so this family is `直接兼容` with the LUTurbo/Lottable `查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿` path. This is a strict single-variable step inside the target `<0.5x` region: estimated selection cost stays at the EF=1 topk baseline, deployment lookup rises with `K`, and combined cost should land near 0.41x, filling the gap between the existing 0.38x/0.1968 and 0.44x/0.1635 topk points. Recent `factorized_topk` rounds improved FVU only slightly while increasing runtime cost, so the cleaner frontier-building move is to continue the already monotone-improving topk K ladder.	This is intentionally conservative: it does not open a new family, and it relies on the existing topk trend rather than a new mechanism. The tradeoff is that it will not teach much about new structure, but that is acceptable here because the current priority is to strengthen the `<0.5x` Pareto frontier with a deployable, directly compatible point and to avoid recipes that slow training without a commensurate FVU gain.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0250_standard_1774702476.log
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0224.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM","value":"96"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r β_r u_r + Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库、{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算 trunk 系数 β_r 与 residual 稀疏系数 α_i，再执行 trunk 查表 + residual 查表 + 加权求和，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。r223 已确认 `topk@EF1,K248` 的 recipe 轴继续向上推 LR 只带来更差 FVU 和明显更差吞吐，说明当前 <0.5x 最强 topk 锚点已基本饱和；同时 r221 说明直接压 `TRUNK_RANK` 会破坏 lowrank_factorized_residual 的 trunk 表达。基于 r210 这个高质量参考点，本轮严格只改一个 env 参数 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`，保留 `K=64, EF=1, signum, LR=3e-3` 与完整 trunk 分支不变，用更短的 factorized scorer 链路替代默认较宽隐藏层，测试是否能把该 family 的 total_cost 从 0.69x 压到约 0.48x，同时尽量保留显著优于同成本 topk 的 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 在约 0.48x 成本下仍明显优于 `topk@0.48x` 的 FVU=0.1483，且训练吞吐没有像 r221 那样恶化，则下一轮相对本轮继续单变量下探到 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=64`，寻找更低成本拐点。","如果 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 的 FVU 明显退化到接近或差于同成本 topk，则说明该 family 的优势主要来自更宽 scorer 而非 trunk 本身；下一轮应关闭这条 scorer 压缩线，转向新的低成本 family。","如果该配置质量接近 r210 但系统代价明显更差，则保留其为解释性对照，不继续把该 family 作为 <0.5x 主战场。"],"notes_to_memory":["r223 给出明确负面信号：`topk@EF1,K248` 的向上 LR 分支已不值得继续，后续应把注意力从 topk recipe 清洗转回新低成本结构。","本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 的 combined_ratio 约为 0.48x，已进入当前重点搜索区间，而不需要再次牺牲 trunk。","与压 `TRUNK_RANK` 不同，压 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM` 只缩短 factorized scorer 链路，保留 trunk 静态库的容量，更符合当前“降低选择成本但不破坏导出结构”的目标。"],"reference_round":210,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效参考轮 r210 只改 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`，family、K、EF、optimizer、LR 及其他结构参数全部不变。选择 96 而不是 128，是因为 128 只会把总成本压到约 0.50x 边界，仍不够明确进入当前主目标区；选择 96 而不是更激进的 64，则是为了先做最小但有效的 scorer 压缩，尽量保留 r210 已证明存在的质量优势。","summary":"相对 r210 的 `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1` 做一次严格 param_only 低成本压缩，仅设置 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`，验证保留完整 trunk 时，缩短 factorized scorer 链路能否把该 family 推入 `<0.5x` Pareto 主前沿。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0171.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost remains within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether removing the second residual refinement stage preserves enough quality and runtime efficiency to justify continued attention as a cheaper compatible branch, or whether the second stage is clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, close this parent branch for the current low-EF regime and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a cheaper compatible Pareto branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly very close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; no decoder basis depends on the input.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality gains with worse runtime are negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. The previous attempt on this family was policy-rejected rather than scientifically resolved, so the highest-value action is to rerun the same matched probe cleanly instead of opening another new family. `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest cheaper compatible parent and directly tests whether the second sparse stage is actually earning its extra cost in the current deployable low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether the cheaper one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
