research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0009.json:81:    "self_review": "This is the right next bet because the current mainline finally has momentum and deserves capacity scaling before any lower-K or cost tradeoffs. The main risk is that extra capacity may give only marginal quality gains relative to added memory and compute.",
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0009.json:104:      "Round 9 escalates capacity within the leading family by testing expansion_factor=16 at fixed K=128 and Adam before considering any lower-K or cost-driven moves."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 56 answered the loss question on the strengthened `gated` recipe cleanly enough: removing the auxiliary term finished essentially flat-to-worse (`0.142968` vs the `0.142923` anchor), so the mainline recipe remains `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. With LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess now all re-checked on the active family, the next single question in the prescribed order is back on the K axis: if we keep the finalized `gated` recipe fixed and reduce only `K` from `128` to `96`, does the lower-cost point still reproduce a healthy full training curve under the now-settled mainline recipe, or was the earlier `K=96` result partly specific to an intermediate recipe-validation phase?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `k`. It also follows the required sequencing: the mainline recipe has now been re-localized on LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess, so returning to K is the clean next step. The main risk is spending a round on confirmation rather than frontier expansion, but after four consecutive non-improving recipe probes the most useful next question is whether the first lower-cost operating point is stable under the finalized recipe rather than only under the earlier sweep context.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 showed that on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor, removing the auxiliary loss is neutral-to-slightly-worse (`0.142968` vs `0.142923`), so `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` should remain part of the strengthened mainline recipe.","Round 57 returns to the K axis under the now-settled `gated` recipe by rechecking `K=96` at fixed `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and `EF=12`, with emphasis on whether the full curve remains clean and deployment-relevant."],"next_hypotheses":["If the refreshed `gated@96` run reproduces a healthy curve near or better than the existing `0.160940` point, treat the lower-cost frontier as stable and continue down the K ladder only if a further deployment question remains.","If `gated@96` degrades materially relative to its existing frontier point, investigate whether the earlier K sweep was less stable than it appeared before making more low-K conclusions."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0114.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk、soft codebook、两阶段 residual 都对应静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；该 family 属于扩展兼容。Round 112 与 Round 113 已在 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=2.4e-3 下复现同一可行 Pareto 点，说明成本预算内的 clean baseline 已确认；本轮只改一个主变量 `LR`，上探到 3.0e-3，回答唯一问题：在 EF=2 的低成本 regime 下，略高一步长能否在不牺牲稳定性和吞吐的前提下改善全程下降形状或终点 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 改善终点或明显加快早中期下降且运行代价未恶化，则将其作为新的 signum 主线学习率候选并考虑一次复现确认。","如果 `LR=3.0e-3` 出现震荡、退化或吞吐/总时长明显变差，则关闭向上 LR 分支，保留 `LR=2.4e-3` 作为 EF=2 主线锚点。","在 LR 轴结论明确前，不切换 optimizer、不改 K，也不改其他成本相关结构参数。"],"notes_to_memory":["兼容性判断：`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 为扩展兼容；导出形式仍是 trunk 库 + codebook 库 + residual 字典库的有限加权和。","EF=2 已在 Round 112 和 Round 113 下稳定落在选择成本预算内，当前 frontier 可行点为 cost≈1.25x、FVU≈0.05914。","本轮遵守单变量原则，只改 `lr`；重点同时观察曲线形状、`tokens_per_sec`、总耗时与 `final_total_tokens`，避免为微小 FVU 改善付出过高运行代价。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"这符合当前主线顺序：EF 已确认可行，clean baseline 已补齐，下一步应只做学习率局部化。选择向上探测而不是改 optimizer，是因为现有 EF=2 曲线已稳定但仍有继续下降迹象，最值得先测试的是更积极一步长是否能带来更好的收敛效率；同时没有引入第二个变量，归因清晰。","summary":"在已确认成本可行且可复现的 `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` EF=2 主线上，仅将 `LR` 从 `2.4e-3` 上调到 `3.0e-3`，测试更高 signum 步长能否改善低成本 regime 的收敛曲线和终点 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0002.json:73:      "Established full K=128 topk anchor is FVU 0.18532327562570572; future lower-K or cost-driven moves should clear that quality bar first.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` was the first recent matched probe to land relatively close to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, so the next most informative architecture-only question is whether that coarse static codebook branch remains viable when the sparse residual selector is made cheaper. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` preserves the same LUTurbo-compatible static-library decomposition as the soft-codebook probe, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection. If it stays reasonably close under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then this family may offer a better quality-versus-online-selection-cost tradeoff than the mainline; if it falls back to the weaker grouped-single-stage pattern, then the earlier soft-codebook result should be treated as requiring full global selection to matter.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. It is a stronger LUTurbo-aligned probe than opening a heavier two-stage soft-codebook branch, because grouped local competition directly targets lower online selection cost while retaining the promising coarse static codebook decomposition seen in Round 92. The risk is that the grouped selector may erase most of the quality gain that made `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` interesting, in which case this family should be deprioritized quickly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 93 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for combining a coarse static codebook branch with cheaper group-local sparse selection; the key question is whether the Round 92 soft-codebook signal survives a more deployment-friendly selector.","Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome; do not turn this into a multi-round soft-codebook branch sequence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly weaker than both `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` and the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard grouped soft-codebook variants and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` remains surprisingly close to the mainline, record it as a potentially lower-selection-cost branch but still return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:13:{"event_id": "evt_1774027054536357788", "ts": 1774027054, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 2, "session_id": "019d0c3d-1937-70c0-a342-12790a584cca", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c3d-1937-70c0-a342-12790a584cca", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "parameter_only", "expected_win": "lower_fvu", "hypothesis": "The new JumpReLU family deserves its first proxy measurement at the K=128 quality anchor; learnable thresholds with smooth gating may suppress weak activations and beat plain TopK FVU before any cost-oriented moves."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:110:{"event_id": "evt_1774030126204469931", "ts": 1774030126, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 9, "session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "cost", "hypothesis": "The current best JumpReLU configuration may retain enough selectivity at K=64 to improve cost meaningfully while staying close enough to the K=128 quality regime to identify whether this family has a viable smaller-K path."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:131:{"event_id": "evt_1774030420638497565", "ts": 1774030420, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 10, "session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "cost", "hypothesis": "JumpReLU may still deliver a usable smaller-K regime at K=32, and measuring that directly is the highest-value next step now that K=64 stayed stable enough to earn a full run."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:208:{"event_id": "evt_1774031436135419778", "ts": 1774031436, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 14, "session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "quality", "hypothesis": "JumpReLU at K=128 may be paying unnecessary reconstruction cost to the auxiliary dead-feature objective, and removing auxk pressure could lower primary FVU below the current 0.1724 full frontier."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:446:{"event_id": "evt_1774060313705784597", "ts": 1774060313, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 32, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime."}}
research/history_archive/rollback_to_pre_round38_20260321_124110/timeline.jsonl:537:{"event_id": "evt_1774061974833512932", "ts": 1774061974, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 37, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "pareto", "hypothesis": "Now that gated holds the full frontier at K=128, K=64, and K=32, the next informative move is to test whether the low-K regime is over-capacitated rather than quality-limited. Reducing gated expansion_factor from 16 to 8 at K=32 may preserve most of the newly won quality while improving cost signals and possibly sharpening feature competition enough to strengthen the Pareto tradeoff."}}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 45 showed that the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) transfers from `K=128` down to `K=96`, improving the prior `gated@96` result while keeping a smooth, still-improving curve. The next single question is whether that gain carries one more step down the cost ladder: if we hold the improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `64`, can `gated` produce a clearly better lower-cost point than the old `K=64` result, or does the Hadamard benefit fade before this support level?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `96` to `64` to test whether the new recipe yields a stronger lower-cost deployment point at the next allowed support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if it stays smooth and finishes materially below the old `gated@64` control (`0.195828`), the improved recipe is genuinely useful beyond the `K=128` anchor; if it falls back toward the old curve, treat the current gain as mainly a high-K effect.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the current mainline family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the prescribed order because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been answered on this recipe, and Round 45 provided positive evidence that the improved recipe transfers at least to `K=96`. The main risk is that `K=64` may sit past the regime where Hadamard helps, but that is the highest-value remaining single-question probe for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 43-45 established a stronger `gated` mainline recipe: `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, with reproducible improvement at `K=128` and successful transfer to `K=96`.","Round 46 isolates the next deployment-relevant K question by testing whether that improved recipe also lowers `gated@64` enough to strengthen the lower-cost part of the frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@64` clearly beats the old `K=64` result with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=32` under the same recipe to locate where the transfer breaks.","If `K=64` regresses toward the old control or shows weaker curve quality, stop the downward sweep and treat the improved recipe mainly as a `K=96/128` high-quality lane."],"primary_variable":"k"}
