research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0221.json:36:      "\u672c\u5730 `selection_cost_estimate()` \u663e\u793a `lowrank_factorized_residual@K64,EF1,TRUNK_RANK=32` \u7684 combined_ratio \u7ea6\u4e3a 0.36x\uff0c\u663e\u8457\u4f4e\u4e8e r210 \u7684 0.69x\uff0c\u4e5f\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d `topk@K248,EF1` \u7684 0.49x\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0221.json:62:    "description": "\u590d\u8dd1 r220 \u7684\u79d1\u5b66\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u4f46\u6309\u5408\u6cd5 `param_only` \u5f62\u5f0f\u4e25\u683c\u951a\u5b9a\u6709\u6548\u53c2\u8003\u8f6e r210\uff0c\u4ec5\u4e0b\u53d1 `TRUNK_RANK=32`\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u5148\u505a\u53c2\u6570\u751f\u6548\u786e\u8ba4\uff0c\u518d\u8bc4\u4f30 lowrank_factorized_residual \u662f\u5426\u80fd\u4ee5\u7ea6 0.36x total_cost \u8fdb\u5165 <0.5x Pareto \u4e3b\u524d\u6cbf\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0207.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"quality_anchor_near_low_cost_boundary","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；在线只做单样本 top-k 选择，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时就是单库查表 + 加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。上一轮 factorized_topk 的 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 降本尝试被 policy 拦截，且当前 <0.5x 区域 FVU 明显受 scorer 容量限制；因此本轮固定 K=64、EF=2、optimizer、LR，仅把 architecture 从 factorized_topk 切到 topk，验证去掉低秩 scorer bottleneck 后，是否能在接近低开销边界的总成本下显著改善 FVU。预计 total_cost 约 0.56x，虽略高于 0.5x，但可作为最邻近的质量锚点，帮助判断 <0.5x 区域的主要瓶颈是否来自 factorization。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 topk@K64 相比 factorized_topk@K64 明显改善 FVU，则说明当前低开销区主要受低秩 scorer 限制，下一步应考虑在更接近 0.5x 的边界上探索更轻但非 factorized 的选择机制。","如果 topk@K64 提升有限，则说明问题主要来自预算本身而非 factorized scorer，下一步应转向新的低成本 family 或更激进的小库/小K 结构，而不是继续在 scorer 形态上纠缠。"],"notes_to_memory":["topk 是最干净的直接兼容单库基线，可用于判断 factorized_topk 在低成本区的 FVU 损失到底有多少来自 scorer factorization。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 这个当前最佳 <0.5x 邻近点的查表预算不变，便于归因。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案严格满足单变量原则，并针对 r206 的 policy_reject 与当前开放假设做了最小转向。代价是总成本会从 0.44x 上升到约 0.56x，不能直接补 <0.5x 前沿，但它能高信息量地判断 factorized scorer 是否是低开销区 FVU 过差的主因。","summary":"切换到直接兼容的 topk family，固定 K=64、EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，获得一个贴近低开销边界的质量锚点，用来判断去掉 factorized scorer 后 FVU 能提升多少。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0147.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002low-rank trunk \u57fa\u5e93 U\u3001soft codebook \u9759\u6001\u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u53ef\u79bb\u7ebf\u5bfc\u51fa\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u6620\u5c04\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u65f6 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002r145 \u8868\u660e\u628a signum \u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u4ece\u4e3b\u7ebf\u53c2\u8003\u503c 3.0e-3 \u5c0f\u5e45\u4e0a\u8c03\u5230 3.3e-3 \u540e\uff0cFVU \u4ece 0.058106 \u964d\u5230 0.057939\uff0c\u4e14\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u672a\u6076\u5316\uff1br146 \u7684 policy_reject \u8bf4\u660e\u4e0d\u80fd\u628a\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u5305\u88c5\u6210 clean baseline\uff0c\u672c\u8f6e\u5fc5\u987b\u7ee7\u7eed\u4f5c\u4e3a\u5355\u53d8\u91cf LR \u95ee\u9898\u5904\u7406\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u76f8\u5bf9\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9\u7684 LR=3.0e-3\uff0c\u628a LR \u6539\u4e3a 3.3e-3 \u7684\u6536\u76ca\u662f\u5426\u53ef\u91cd\u590d\u6210\u7acb\uff0c\u5e76\u4e14\u4e0d\u4f1a\u4ee5\u66f4\u5dee\u7684 tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u6216 final_total_tokens \u4e3a\u4ee3\u4ef7\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0062.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline stalled for nine rounds, the highest-value Round 62 matched architecture probe is `group_topk`: it preserves the same static decoder-library weighted-sum export contract and fixed `K=128`, while changing only support formation to a group-local winner scheme that could reduce selection complexity if reconstruction stays competitive. This probe answers one question only: is `group_topk` intrinsically strong enough under the matched `signum`/`2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe to merit any later follow-up.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `group_topk` and keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This respects the Round 62 policy: one probe only, one main variable only, and the full mainline recipe stays matched except for architecture. `group_topk` is a better probe than heavier multi-branch variants because it is directly LUTurbo-compatible and has a plausible path to lower online selection cost rather than only improving training-side expressiveness.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 62 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `group_topk` rather than expanding the search broadly.","`group_topk` remains directly compatible with LUTurbo because reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library; only the encoder-side selection rule changes.","The main deployment-relevant reason to test `group_topk` is not just FVU but whether grouped winner selection looks promising enough to justify later work on lower selection overhead under the same decoder contract."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` is clearly worse than matched `gated` at `K=128`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `group_topk` is roughly competitive, record it as a potentially deployment-friendlier selector but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `group_topk` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0128.json:19:    "hypothesis": "最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。r127 的 matched probe 说明两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下仍有真实 FVU 价值，但其 selection_cost 明显高于单阶段父节点；因此本轮回到主线 family，只改 NUM_CODES=32，测试是否能在保持两阶段结构优势的同时压低 encoder 选择成本，缩小与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 的成本差距。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0128.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_selection_cost",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0128.json:57:      "本轮只改 NUM_CODES，目标不是追更低绝对 FVU，而是测试两阶段主线能否改善 selection_cost/FVU Pareto。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0128.json:58:      "评估时必须同时记录 selection_cost、FVU、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，避免把更长训练误判为结构收益。"
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0128.json:61:      "若 NUM_CODES=32 仅小幅伤害 FVU 但显著降低 selection_cost，则继续沿 num_codes 轴补一个中间点细化 Pareto。",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0174.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; grouped competition changes only how residual support is selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should remain within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget because it reuses the feasible `lowrank_residual` scorer stack and only constrains support selection. The single question is whether group-local residual competition is intrinsically worth keeping in the low-EF deployable regime, or whether even this cheaper selector simplification is clearly inferior to the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, discard grouped low-rank residual variants and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a lower-complexity compatible reserve branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selector complexity, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static residual dictionary; grouped competition affects only online selection, not decoder exportability.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; a tiny quality change with slower runtime is negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. After the recent soft-codebook selector probes did not pressure the mainline, the highest-value remaining budget-feasible matched probe is `lowrank_grouped_residual`: it avoids the repeated controller issue seen on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, keeps the export contract simple, and tests whether local competition can buy meaningful runtime simplicity without collapsing quality in the current low-EF regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether a grouped low-rank single-stage residual architecture is worth any continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:208:      "design_hypothesis": "On the directly compatible `topk` line, increasing `K` from 96 to 160 should produce a materially better `<0.5x` Pareto point, likely around the low-0.18 FVU range at about 0.41x total_cost, while avoiding the recent `factorized_topk` pattern of modest quality gains paired with worse throughput.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:374:        "If `topk` K=160 underperforms the monotone trend, shift the next round to a different directly compatible low-cost selector family instead of continuing dense K sweeps.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:375:        "If runtime regresses disproportionately at K=160, treat that as a system-side warning and prefer lower-cost frontier densification over larger-K topk pushes."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:575:        "\u7ee7\u7eed\u907f\u514d routed \u4e0e bucketed matched probe\uff0c\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u4eec\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u8d85\u8fc7 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n \u9884\u7b97\u3002"
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:819:        "If matched `routed` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because decoupled routing may better align with LUTurbo online-cost goals.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:890:      "design_hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: codebook_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_m \u03c0_m c_m + \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff1b\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u5b9e\u73b0\u91cc\u524d\u5411\u4e3b\u8def\u5f84\u7b49\u4ef7\u4e8e x_hat = c_m* + \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {c_m} \u662f\u9759\u6001 coarse codebook\uff0c{b_i} \u662f\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u3002\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u65f6\uff0c\u53ef\u5b9e\u73b0\u4e3a\u4e00\u6b21 coarse \u5b50\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u4e00\u6b21 residual \u7a00\u758f\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\uff0c\u6700\u7ec8\u4ecd\u662f\u591a\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r233 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `ARCHITECTURE=codebook_topk`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `K=32`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003`\u3001`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u201c\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001 coarse codebook + \u5c0f K residual\u201d\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u7ea6 0.38x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u5904\uff0c\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e\u540c\u6210\u672c plain topk \u7684 FVU\uff0c\u5e76\u6bd4\u6700\u8fd1\u5df2\u7ed9\u51fa\u8d1f\u4fe1\u53f7\u7684 factorized/grouped/JumpReLU \u5c0f\u4fee\u7ebf\u66f4\u6709\u7ed3\u6784\u4fe1\u606f\u91cf\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u6cbf JumpReLU bandwidth \u5fae\u8c03\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a r234 \u867d\u628a FVU \u538b\u5230 0.14545\uff0c\u4f46\u603b\u65f6\u957f\u66b4\u6da8\u5230 899s\uff0c\u5df2\u6784\u6210\u660e\u786e\u8d1f\u9762\u7cfb\u7edf\u4fe1\u53f7\uff1b\u800c `codebook_topk@EF1,K32` \u6839\u636e\u672c\u5730 `selection_cost_estimate()` \u7ea6\u4e3a sel=0.28x\u3001deploy=0.09x\u3001total=0.38x\uff0c\u6b63\u843d\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u6218\u533a\u95f4\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1078:      "design_hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_residual_vq` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `c_m` is one selected codebook vector from a static coarse library, and the residual term is a weighted sum over a static residual dictionary. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9` because LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors, coarse codebook, and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + coarse code lookup + sparse residual lookups + weighted sum` online. The single question for this probe is whether replacing the soft coarse branch with a hard VQ-style coarse branch is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime. This should stay inside the encoder-cost budget at `EF=2`, so it is likely to produce a real training/runtime signal rather than another policy reject.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1099:        "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1100:        "If `lowrank_residual_vq` underperforms the mainline on FVU or slows training without a compensating runtime/quality benefit, mark hard-VQ coarse branches as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1108:      "design_hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the JumpReLU selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and their coefficients. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then execute `trunk lookup + thresholded sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The probe asks one question only: in the low-EF feasible regime, does learned thresholding provide a better architecture tradeoff than the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline, or should this family be ruled out. Encoder selection cost should stay in the feasible band at `EF=2`, so this should produce a real signal instead of a policy reject.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1137:        "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1138:        "If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` underperforms the mainline on FVU or shows materially worse `tokens_per_sec`/runtime without compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-cost regime."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1185:        "\u7ee7\u7eed\u907f\u514d routed \u4e0e bucketed matched probe\uff0c\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u4eec\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u8d85\u8fc7 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n \u9884\u7b97\u3002"
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1193:      "design_hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; grouped competition changes only how residual support is selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should remain within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget because it reuses the feasible `lowrank_residual` scorer stack and only constrains support selection. The single question is whether group-local residual competition is intrinsically worth keeping in the low-EF deployable regime, or whether even this cheaper selector simplification is clearly inferior to the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1224:      "design_hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 probe family \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff1b\u5176\u4e2d low-rank trunk \u9879 U(Vx) \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0cresidual \u5206\u652f \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u4e0a\u7684\u7a00\u758f\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u80fd\u591f\u843d\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u2018\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u2019\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e3b\u5047\u8bbe\uff1a\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5b8c\u5168 matched \u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u53bb\u6389 soft codebook coarse branch \u540e\uff0clowrank_residual \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u4f5c\u4e3a\u66f4\u4f4e encoder selection cost \u7684\u6781\u7b80\u517c\u5bb9\u652f\u7ebf\uff1b\u82e5 FVU \u76f8\u6bd4\u4e3b\u7ebf\u4e0e lowrank_soft_codebook_residual \u90fd\u660e\u663e\u6076\u5316\uff0c\u5219\u8bf4\u660e coarse codebook \u5206\u652f\u672c\u8eab\u662f\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u4e0d\u53ef\u7f3a\u5c11\u7684\u7ed3\u6784\u589e\u76ca\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1278:        "\u82e5 lowrank_residual \u5728\u66f4\u4f4e selection_cost \u4e0b\u4ecd\u4fdd\u6301\u53ef\u63a5\u53d7 FVU \u4e14\u8bad\u7ec3\u66f4\u5feb\uff0c\u53ef\u5c06\u5176\u4fdd\u7559\u4e3a\u66f4\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u7684\u517c\u5bb9\u5907\u9009\u652f\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1279:        "\u7ee7\u7eed\u907f\u514d routed \u4e0e bucketed matched probe\uff0c\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u4eec\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u8d85\u8fc7 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n \u9884\u7b97\u3002"
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1634:      "design_hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\uff1b\u5176\u4e2d low-rank trunk \u5e93 U\u3001\u9759\u6001 soft-codebook \u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u53ef\u9759\u6001\u5bfc\u51fa\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u6620\u5c04\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b encoder selection_cost \u4ecd\u5728 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u5185\uff0c\u4e14\u8fde\u7eed 3 \u8f6e\u56f4\u7ed5 `NUM_CODES` \u538b\u7f29\u90fd\u6ca1\u6709\u6539\u53d8\u66f2\u7ebf\u7ec8\u70b9\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u5f53\u524d\u74f6\u9888\u66f4\u53ef\u80fd\u5728\u4f18\u5316\u52a8\u6001\u800c\u4e0d\u662f coarse codebook \u5bb9\u91cf\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u628a\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\u5207\u5230 `optimizer`\uff0c\u5e76\u4f7f\u7528\u66f4\u4fdd\u5b88\u7684 `adam@1.0e-3`\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 family/EF/K \u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\u6539\u5584\u8bad\u7ec3\u66f2\u7ebf\u5f62\u72b6\u6216\u7ec8\u70b9 FVU\uff0c\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u5728 signum \u914d\u65b9\u5468\u56f4\u5f97\u5230\u540c\u6837\u7684 plateau\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1821:      "design_hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, where the bucket gate only changes stage-1/2 selector scores and all decoded terms still come from static libraries `{U,V}`, codebook `C`, and residual dictionary `B`. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9` with a clean LUTurbo export path, but the matched EF=2 selector is likely not worth continuing because bucketed dual scorers raise encoder selection cost to about `2.5x h\u00d7n`, so the policy should reject it before spending a long training run.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1825:        "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune one cost knob at a time (`TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`) to improve the feasible Pareto point without changing architecture.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1826:        "If a future bucketed revisit is desired, only do it as a cost-reduction study on the bucketed family itself with primary variable `TRUNK_RANK` or `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`, not as another matched-architecture probe."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1834:      "design_hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction remains `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`; routing only perturbs stage-1/stage-2 support selection scores, while all decoded terms still come from static trunk, codebook, and residual libraries. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9` because LUTurbo/Lottable can export the low-rank trunk matrices, soft codebook vectors, and residual dictionary once, then execute `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + routed support selection + weighted sparse lookups + sum` online. The key question is whether router-driven support allocation is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime. Current cost accounting strongly suggests no: adding two full routers likely pushes encoder selection cost above the `1.5x h\u00d7n` hard cap, so the most informative outcome is a quick policy gate that rules this family out as a mainline candidate at `EF=2`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1838:        "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/memory.json:1839:        "If this routed matched probe is policy-rejected as expected, mark routed two-stage soft-codebook as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime unless a future single-variable cost-reduction round explicitly targets router cost."
