research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0157.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u8be5 family \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u4e2d U(Vx) \u53ef\u79bb\u7ebf\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c{c_m} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 soft-codebook \u5e93\uff0c{b_i} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u4ecd\u662f\u591a\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b\u7684 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002r153-r155 \u5df2\u5148\u540e\u8865\u9f50 clean baseline \u5e76\u628a signum \u7684 LR \u66f2\u7ebf\u770b\u6e05\uff0c3.3e-3 \u867d\u6709\u5c0f\u5e45\u7a33\u5b9a\u6536\u76ca\uff0c\u4f46\u5f53\u524d\u7b56\u7565\u987a\u5e8f\u8981\u6c42\u5728 LR \u4e4b\u540e\u5148\u56de\u7b54 optimizer \u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u4e14 r156 \u7684 K \u8f74\u5c1d\u8bd5\u5df2\u88ab policy \u62e6\u622a\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf OPTIMIZER\uff1a\u4fdd\u6301 family\u3001EF\u3001K\u3001LR \u4e0e\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u4ec5\u5c06\u4f18\u5316\u5668\u4ece signum \u5207\u5230 adam\uff0c\u56de\u7b54\u552f\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728\u540c\u6837\u7684\u53ef\u90e8\u7f72\u4f4e\u6210\u672c regime \u4e0b\uff0coptimizer \u672c\u8eab\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u6709\u503c\u5f97\u4fdd\u7559\u7684\u66f2\u7ebf\u5f62\u72b6\u6216\u7ec8\u70b9\u4fe1\u53f7\uff0c\u8fd8\u662f\u5e94\u88ab\u518d\u6b21\u660e\u786e\u5173\u95ed\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0157.json:52:      "EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u4ecd\u5728\u9884\u7b97\u5185\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u4e0d\u6539 EF\u3001K\u3001TRUNK_RANK\u3001NUM_CODES \u6216\u5176\u4ed6\u6210\u672c\u8f74\uff0c\u53ea\u9694\u79bb optimizer \u6548\u5e94\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0230.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u53c2\u4e0e\u5355\u6837\u672c\u5728\u7ebf\u6253\u5206\u4e0e top-k \u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 r219 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`K=256`\u3001`signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u628a scorer \u94fe\u8def\u4ece\u9ed8\u8ba4\u5bbd hidden \u5927\u5e45\u538b\u7f29\u540e\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u628a\u8be5 family \u7684 total_cost \u538b\u5230\u7ea6 0.40x\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u4ecd\u9760\u6ee1\u67e5\u8868\u652f\u6301\u9884\u7b97\u83b7\u5f97\u660e\u663e\u4f18\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e\u6210\u672c topk \u524d\u6cbf\u7684 FVU\u3002\u8fd9\u4e2a\u65b9\u5411\u7684\u4ef7\u503c\u5728\u4e8e\u5b83\u76f4\u63a5\u56de\u7b54\u5f53\u524d\u9636\u6bb5\u6700\u91cd\u8981\u7684\u4f4e\u5f00\u9500\u95ee\u9898\u4e4b\u4e00\uff1a\u66f4\u77ed\u7684\u9009\u62e9\u94fe\u8def\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u4e0d\u727a\u7272 LUTurbo \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u6027\u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u5f62\u6210\u6bd4 plain topk \u66f4\u597d\u7684 cost-FVU \u6743\u8861\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0230.json:37:      "\u672c\u5730 `selection_cost_estimate()` \u663e\u793a `factorized_topk@EF1,K256,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` \u7684 combined_ratio \u7ea6\u4e3a 0.40x\uff0c\u8fdc\u4f4e\u4e8e\u9ed8\u8ba4\u5bbd scorer \u914d\u7f6e\uff0c\u6b63\u597d\u843d\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u91cd\u70b9\u641c\u7d22\u533a\u95f4\u3002"
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0244.json:20:    "summary": "\u4e25\u683c\u951a\u5b9a r242\uff0c\u4ec5\u5207\u5230 `factorized_topk`\uff0c\u5728\u7ea6 0.38x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u4f4d\u7f6e\u6d4b\u8bd5 factorized scorer \u662f\u5426\u80fd\u6bd4 `topk@K96` \u7ed9\u51fa\u66f4\u597d\u7684 cost-FVU \u6743\u8861\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u68c0\u67e5\u5b83\u662f\u5426\u907f\u514d\u4e86\u8fd1\u671f plain topk \u4e2d\u6bb5 K \u626b\u63cf\u5e26\u6765\u7684\u8fd0\u884c\u65f6\u4ee3\u4ef7\u4e0a\u5347\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0244.json:22:    "expected_win": "better_fvu_within_low_cost_region",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0244.json:62:    "description": "\u4e25\u683c\u951a\u5b9a r242\uff0c\u4ec5\u5207\u5230 `factorized_topk`\uff0c\u5728\u7ea6 0.38x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u4f4d\u7f6e\u6d4b\u8bd5 factorized scorer \u662f\u5426\u80fd\u6bd4 `topk@K96` \u7ed9\u51fa\u66f4\u597d\u7684 cost-FVU \u6743\u8861\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u68c0\u67e5\u5b83\u662f\u5426\u907f\u514d\u4e86\u8fd1\u671f plain topk \u4e2d\u6bb5 K \u626b\u63cf\u5e26\u6765\u7684\u8fd0\u884c\u65f6\u4ee3\u4ef7\u4e0a\u5347\u3002",
research/history_archive/01_20260320_175012/memory.json:2:  "current_focus": "Treat K=128 only as the initial search anchor, not as a success criterion. The research objective is to find configurations whose FVU is dramatically better than the current K=128 baseline, with a target on the order of halving that baseline FVU before rewarding smaller K or lower cost.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/memory.json:2:  "current_focus": "Treat K=128 only as the initial search anchor, not as a success criterion. The research objective is to find configurations whose FVU is dramatically better than the current K=128 baseline, with a target on the order of halving that baseline FVU before rewarding smaller K or lower cost.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/memory.json:2548:        "hypothesis": "Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/memory.json:2655:        "hypothesis": "Stability has been restored on the gated path, and the `AUXK_ALPHA=0` K=128 run essentially matched the prior best full result, so the safest informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost Pareto point under the same newly revalidated regime. Changing only K from 128 to 64 tests whether the aux-free gated recipe can strengthen the lower-K frontier without reopening unstable architecture paths.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/memory.json:2666:        "hypothesis": "The standard gated hyperparameter sweeps at K=128 are exhausted and the recent `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` recovery check regressed, so the cleanest exploitation move is to reuse the best validated aux-free gated regime and probe the remaining adjacent lower-K point. Changing only K from the strongest K=128 anchor to K=32 tests whether the recovered gated recipe can strengthen the low-cost front\n[truncated for compact history]",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/memory.json:2941:        "original_hypothesis": "Stability has returned on the gated path, and the K=64 point was reconfirmed exactly in both proxy and full. The next least-risk informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost gated Pareto point at K=32 under the same strongest regime, keep\n[truncated for compact history]",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0237.json:22:    "expected_win": "better_fvu_within_low_cost_region",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0237.json:36:      "\u672c\u5730 `selection_cost_estimate()` \u663e\u793a `factorized_topk@EF1,K256,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384` \u7684 combined_ratio \u7ea6\u4e3a 0.44x\uff0c\u4ecd\u7a33\u5728\u5f53\u524d `<0.5x` \u4e3b\u6218\u533a\uff1b\u76f8\u8f83 r230 \u7684 `FHD=96`\uff08\u7ea6 0.30x\uff09\uff0c\u8fd9\u662f\u4e00\u6b21\u7528\u66f4\u591a scorer \u5bb9\u91cf\u6362\u53d6\u8d28\u91cf\u3001\u4f46\u4ecd\u4e0d\u56de\u5230 full-width topk \u7684\u5e72\u51c0 probe\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0089.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_cost",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0089.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_residual` is the strongest remaining LUTurbo-aligned probe because it is the simplest low-rank static-library decomposition still comparable to the current mainline, and it directly tests whether the second residual pass is buying necessary quality or only extra online cost. The main risk is that the family may underfit badly at matched K128, but that negative result would still answer the exact worth-continuing question cleanly.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0089.json:52:      "Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for the simplest low-rank single-stage residual decomposition; the core question is whether dropping the second residual stage can preserve enough quality to justify the lower expected online cost.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0089.json:57:      "If `lowrank_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-cost branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0089.json:77:    "self_review": "This obeys the matched architecture probe rule by changing only `architecture` and keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. `lowrank_residual` is the strongest remaining LUTurbo-aligned probe because it is the simplest low-rank static-library decomposition still comparable to the current mainline, and it directly tests whether the second residual pass is buying necessary quality or only extra online cost. The main risk is that the family may underfit badly at matched K128, but that negative result would still answer the exact worth-continuing question cleanly.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0169.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes the single-sample support/coef shaping before top-k, not the exported decoder basis. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a fixed residual vector library, with the learned thresholds used only in online selection. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost should stay within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget and remain below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this thresholded low-rank single-stage selector is intrinsically worth keeping in the current low-EF deployable regime, or whether the mainline\u2019s soft-codebook plus two-stage refinement remains clearly necessary.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0169.json:53:      "Judge family worthiness using `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside final FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total online/runtime cost rather than FVU alone."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0169.json:58:      "If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/round_summaries/round_0052.json:60:    "self_review": "This keeps the round to one parameter, stays within the `EF<=16` cap, preserves the lower-K target, and follows the prescribed post-LR-sweep move after the `LR=4e-4` regression. The main risk is that the family remains weak at `K=40` regardless of modest capacity increases, but `EF=12` is the least-cost informative next point before either concluding the small-EF track is exhausted or probing the even smaller `EF=4` edge.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/round_summaries/round_0052.json:94:      "If `EF=12` materially improves `K=40` proxy quality, decide whether it is strong enough for promotion or whether the remaining `EF=4` point is still worth mapping for the cost-quality frontier.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0149.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u4e2d U(Vx) \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c{c_m} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 soft-codebook \u5e93\uff0c{b_i} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u6700\u7ec8\u4ecd\u662f\u591a\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002r145 \u4e0e r147 \u5df2\u4e24\u6b21\u663e\u793a LR=3.3e-3 \u7684\u7ec8\u70b9 FVU=0.0579389\uff0c\u4f18\u4e8e 3.0e-3 baseline \u7684 0.0581064\uff1b\u800c r148 \u4e0a\u63a2\u5230 3.6e-3 \u540e\u56de\u843d\u5230 0.0581512 \u4e14\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u5347\u81f3 453s\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u7ee7\u7eed\u4e0a\u8c03 LR \u7684\u6536\u76ca\u5df2\u4e0d\u6210\u7acb\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u66f4\u9700\u8981\u56de\u7b54\u7684\u5355\u4e00\u95ee\u9898\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u6269\u5f20\u641c\u7d22\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u786e\u8ba4 3.3e-3 \u8fd9\u4e2a\u66f4\u4f18\u70b9\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u8fd0\u884c\u6ce2\u52a8\u4e0b\u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u80fd\u4ee5\u53ef\u63a5\u53d7\u7684 tokens_per_sec \u4e0e\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u7a33\u5b9a\u590d\u73b0\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u51b3\u5b9a\u662f\u5426\u628a\u5b83\u6b63\u5f0f\u89c6\u4e3a\u4e3b\u7ebf signum \u914d\u65b9\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0149.json:52:      "EF=2 \u7ee7\u7eed\u6ee1\u8db3 selection_cost \u9884\u7b97\uff1bK \u4fdd\u6301 128\uff0c\u907f\u514d\u628a\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u53d8\u5316\u4e0e LR \u590d\u9a8c\u6df7\u6742\u3002",
