research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eighteen straight no-improve rounds mean the recent EF=8 recovery ladder is no longer the right mainline. The least-risk stagnation break is a same-band architecture comparison in the preferred EF=16 regime: run `lowrank_residual` at `K=48` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether the simpler ungated low-rank residual encoder gives a better lower-K quality/cost tradeoff than the recent gated-recovery path.","summary":"Shift from the exhausted EF=8 recovery sweep to a fairer architecture comparison in the allowed main band. Probe `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` in proxy, holding optimizer and LR fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than doing another minor tweak. The main risk is that `K=48` is an interpolated point for `lowrank_residual`, so the read may still be mostly frontier-mapping rather than a direct win, but it is a cleaner informative move than more EF=8 recovery rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"48"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Break the EF=8 recovery loop after 18 no-improve rounds; return to same-EF architecture comparison in the preferred EF=12/16 band.","Use `K=48` as the lower-K comparison point so the round still prioritizes Pareto expansion while switching the primary variable back to architecture."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is competitive, continue the same family downward to `K=40` before reopening optimizer sweeps.","If `lowrank_residual` at `K=48`, `EF=16` is clearly weak, pivot to another fundamentally different existing family in the same `EF=16` band rather than returning to more `lowrank_gated_residual` recovery tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/round_summaries/round_0068.json:54:    "hypothesis": "Eighteen straight no-improve rounds mean the recent EF=8 recovery ladder is no longer the right mainline. The least-risk stagnation break is a same-band architecture comparison in the preferred EF=16 regime: run `lowrank_residual` at `K=48` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to test whether the simpler ungated low-rank residual encoder gives a better lower-K quality/cost tradeoff than the recent gated-recovery path.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0059.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0059.json:85:      "If matched `factorized_topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its scoring path may align better with LUTurbo online-cost goals.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0059.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0181.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the residual coefficients are chosen by a factorized scorer but still decode as a finite weighted sum over a static residual dictionary `B`. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + factorized support scoring + weighted sparse lookup-sum` online. The single question is whether a lower-cost factorized residual selector is worth continuing versus the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline in the low-EF feasible regime. This probe should stay safely within the encoder-cost budget and gives a clean read on whether scorer factorization is a viable architecture direction rather than another likely policy reject.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0181.json:52:      "This matched probe tests a still-compatible low-cost architecture direction that has not recently been revisited under the current `K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3` regime.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0181.json:53:      "Review `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; if factorization only saves selector cost proxy but trains materially slower or reconstructs worse, treat that as a negative signal."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0181.json:56:      "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0181.json:57:      "If `lowrank_factorized_residual` underperforms on FVU and/or slows throughput without a compensating cost advantage, mark factorized residual scoring as not worth continuing in the current low-cost regime."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0171.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one static codebook lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual library, so inference remains a finite weighted sum over fixed vector banks. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost remains within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget and below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether removing the second residual refinement stage preserves enough quality and runtime efficiency to justify continued attention as a cheaper compatible branch, or whether the second stage is clearly necessary.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0171.json:23:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe. The previous attempt on this family was policy-rejected rather than scientifically resolved, so the highest-value action is to rerun the same matched probe cleanly instead of opening another new family. `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest cheaper compatible parent and directly tests whether the second sparse stage is actually earning its extra cost in the current deployable low-EF regime.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0171.json:51:      "Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total runtime cost rather than FVU alone; small quality gains with worse runtime are negative."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0171.json:56:      "If it is unexpectedly very close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0218.json:22:    "expected_win": "better_fvu_within_low_cost_region",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0148.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u4e2d U(Vx) \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff0c{c_m} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 soft-codebook \u5e93\uff0c{b_i} \u4e3a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u6700\u7ec8\u4ecd\u662f\u591a\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u53ef\u6620\u5c04\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u8be5 family \u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002r145 \u4e0e r147 \u5728\u76f8\u540c family/K/EF/optimizer \u4e0b\u4e24\u6b21\u590d\u73b0\u4e86 LR=3.3e-3 \u7684\u66f4\u4f18\u7ec8\u70b9 FVU=0.0579389\uff0c\u76f8\u6bd4 3.0e-3 baseline \u7684 0.0581064 \u662f\u7a33\u5b9a\u6b63\u4fe1\u53f7\uff1b\u540c\u65f6 r147 \u7684\u66f4\u957f\u8017\u65f6\u4e3b\u8981\u6765\u81ea tokens_per_sec \u4ece\u7ea6 166.5k \u964d\u5230 66.6k\uff0c\u800c final_total_tokens \u4ecd\u662f 59,969,536\uff0c\u8bf4\u660e\u8fd9\u6b21\u53d8\u6162\u66f4\u50cf\u8fd0\u884c\u65f6\u541e\u5410\u6ce2\u52a8\uff0c\u4e0d\u5e94\u63d0\u524d\u7ec8\u6b62 LR \u8f74\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 family\u3001EF\u3001K\u3001optimizer \u4e0e\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\u4e0d\u53d8\u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u628a signum \u5b66\u4e60\u7387\u4ece 3.3e-3 \u7ee7\u7eed\u4e0a\u63a2\u5230 3.6e-3\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u8fd8\u80fd\u5ef6\u7eed\u4e2d\u540e\u6bb5\u6536\u655b\u6539\u5584\u5e76\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u538b\u4f4e FVU\uff0c\u8fd8\u662f\u5df2\u7ecf\u5f00\u59cb\u8fdb\u5165\u8fc7\u51b2\u533a\u95f4\u3002",
