research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0156.json:17:    "hypothesis": "\u8be5 family \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u4e2d low-rank trunk \u5e93 U\u3001soft-codebook \u9759\u6001\u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u4ee5\u53ca\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 residual \u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u90fd\u53ef\u79bb\u7ebf\u5bfc\u51fa\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u6700\u7ec8\u4ecd\u662f\u591a\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u843d\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u5f53\u524d EF=2 \u4e0b\u8be5 family \u7684 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u4ecd\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\uff0c\u800c r154-r155 \u5df2\u628a signum \u4e3b\u7ebf LR \u7a33\u5b9a\u5230 3.3e-3\u3002\u65e2\u7136 optimizer \u5206\u652f\u5728 EF=2\u3001\u540c family \u4e0a\u5df2\u51fa\u73b0\u7206\u70b8\u6027\u8d1f\u4fe1\u53f7\uff0closs \u8f74\u4e0e TRUNK_RANK=32 \u4e5f\u672a\u5e26\u6765\u6536\u76ca\uff0c\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a\u66f4\u8d34\u8fd1 LUTurbo \u603b\u5728\u7ebf\u6210\u672c\u7684\u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 family\u3001EF\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u4e0d\u53d8\u65f6\uff0c\u4ec5\u5c06 K \u4ece 128 \u5c0f\u6b65\u4e0b\u8c03\u5230 112\uff0c\u80fd\u5426\u5728\u660e\u663e\u964d\u4f4e\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u7684\u540c\u65f6\uff0c\u628a FVU \u7ef4\u6301\u5728\u63a5\u8fd1\u5f53\u524d 0.05794 \u7684\u6c34\u5e73\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u5f62\u6210\u66f4\u4f18\u7684\u603b\u6210\u672c\u6743\u8861\u70b9\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0156.json:50:      "EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u4ecd\u5728\u9884\u7b97\u5185\uff1b\u672c\u8f6e\u6539 K \u4e0d\u89e6\u78b0 encoder \u6210\u672c\u786c\u7ea6\u675f\uff0c\u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0124.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4fdd\u6301\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_m pi_m c_m + \u03a3_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + \u03a3_j alpha_j^(2) b_j\u3002\u5176\u5bfc\u51fa\u8def\u5f84\u4ecd\u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93 U\u3001\u9759\u6001 soft-codebook \u5e93 {c_m}\u3001\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u5e93 {b_i} \u4e0a\u7684\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u843d\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u5f53\u524d family \u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u7ea6 1.25x\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u5438\u53d6 r123 policy_reject \u7684\u4fe1\u53f7\uff0c\u4e25\u683c\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a\u4e3b\u53d8\u91cf\uff1a\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u4e0d\u53d8\u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u4ec5\u5c06 optimizer \u4ece signum \u5207\u5230 adam\uff0c\u5148\u786e\u8ba4 optimizer \u8f74\u672c\u8eab\u662f\u5426\u53ef\u8dd1\u3001\u66f2\u7ebf\u662f\u5426\u6709\u4ef7\u503c\uff0c\u518d\u51b3\u5b9a\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u5355\u72ec\u4e3a adam \u5f00 LR \u5b50\u626b\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0021.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 20 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=4` is effectively past the practical floor: the late-phase FVU curve flattened completely while dead-feature pressure rose to about `0.68`, so further low-K descent is no longer the right question. This round changes only `K`, moving from the quality anchor side to `K=96`, to test whether LUTurbo can obtain a materially cheaper but still high-quality deployment point that may be more practical than the stressed ultra-low-K regime.","summary":"Shift the K sweep from the collapsed extreme low end to the unexplored moderate-cost region: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and set `K=96` to measure whether a near-anchor quality point exists between the current `K=64` and `K=128` frontier points.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` mainline, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule and allowed-K set, and asks a single clean frontier question. The main risk is that `K=96` may add little beyond interpolation, but after `K=4` and `K=8` showed strong capacity stress, probing the moderate-K gap is a more deployment-relevant use of the same single-axis budget than continuing to push or retread the collapsed low end.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 20 (`K=4`) appears to mark the hard lower bound of the current topk/signum regime: late improvement vanished while `dead_pct` climbed to about `0.68` and `auxk` remained around `0.58`.","The current useful low-K region is likely above `K=8`, with `K=16` looking much more plausible than `K=8` or `K=4` for deployment-aligned tradeoffs.","Given the hard low-end boundary is now mapped, the next most informative single-variable K question is whether `K=96` provides a stronger quality-cost sweet spot between the existing `K=64` and `K=128` points."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=96` is very close to `K=128` in both final FVU and curve shape, it may become the practical high-quality reduced-cost default for this family.","If `K=96` lands roughly on interpolation between `K=64` and `K=128`, the K frontier on this recipe is likely sufficiently mapped and the next round should return to recipe tuning.","If `K=96` underperforms unexpectedly, re-check whether the current topk recipe is over-specialized to either very high or very low K and then move back to one recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0096.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the prescribed mainline order exactly: no new family, no coupled changes, allowed `K`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit. The cost is that this round may not improve the frontier numerically, but establishing a trustworthy baseline is more valuable than opening LR or optimizer tuning on top of a single winning run.",
