research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0235.json:36:      "\u672c\u5730 `selection_cost_estimate()` \u663e\u793a `codebook_topk@EF1,K32` \u7684 combined_ratio \u7ea6\u4e3a 0.38x\uff0c\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d `topk@K248` \u7684 0.49x\uff0c\u4e5f\u660e\u663e\u4f4e\u4e8e `lowrank_factorized_residual@K32` \u7684\u7ea6 0.66x\u3002",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0019.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` now owns the full frontier at K=32, 64, and 128 under the shared EF=16 recipe, so the next clean stabilization move is to test whether a larger sparse residual budget improves quality within this winning family. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=64 may strengthen the middle Pareto point by giving the residual branch more capacity while keeping the low-rank trunk and optimization recipe fixed.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=64` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, holding the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This tests whether extra residual capacity can further improve the newly established lowrank Pareto frontier at the middle K value.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps variable isolation clean and follows the natural next step after mapping the family across K: stabilize an internal capacity axis on a high-value frontier point. The main risk is that EF=16 is already sufficient and EF=32 only adds cost, but this is the most informative single-parameter read before trying aux or revisiting architecture exploration.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 begins family-specific stabilization for `lowrank_residual` after it established full frontier wins at K=32, K=64, and K=128.","The chosen axis is `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, tested at K=64 first because that midpoint best represents whether extra residual capacity improves the practical Pareto frontier rather than only the quality anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves proxy FVU at K=64, promote it to full and then consider the same capacity increase at K=32 or K=128 depending on where the gain is largest.","If EF=32 is flat or worse, keep EF=16 as the mainline and test a different single stabilization axis such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` at K=64 or K=128.","If EF=32 improves quality but causes clear runtime or memory regression, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than discarding the higher-capacity variant outright."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0193.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 probe family \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff1b\u5176\u4e2d low-rank trunk \u9879 U(Vx) \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0cresidual \u5206\u652f \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i \u53ef\u5bfc\u51fa\u4e3a\u9759\u6001 residual \u5b57\u5178\u4e0a\u7684\u7a00\u758f\u52a0\u6743\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u80fd\u591f\u843d\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u2018\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u2019\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e3b\u5047\u8bbe\uff1a\u5728\u4fdd\u6301 K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=2\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5b8c\u5168 matched \u7684\u524d\u63d0\u4e0b\uff0c\u53bb\u6389 soft codebook coarse branch \u540e\uff0clowrank_residual \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u503c\u5f97\u4f5c\u4e3a\u66f4\u4f4e encoder selection cost \u7684\u6781\u7b80\u517c\u5bb9\u652f\u7ebf\uff1b\u82e5 FVU \u76f8\u6bd4\u4e3b\u7ebf\u4e0e lowrank_soft_codebook_residual \u90fd\u660e\u663e\u6076\u5316\uff0c\u5219\u8bf4\u660e coarse codebook \u5206\u652f\u672c\u8eab\u662f\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u4e0d\u53ef\u7f3a\u5c11\u7684\u7ed3\u6784\u589e\u76ca\u3002",
