research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0079.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the Round 79 mainline policy exactly: no new family, no code edit, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit, and the round answers one question only about baseline stability. The cost is that this round may not improve frontier numerically, but establishing a repeatable anchor is higher-value than immediately touching LR after only one winning run on a freshly promoted family.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0079.json:82:    "self_review": "This follows the Round 79 mainline policy exactly: no new family, no code edit, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` is explicit, and the round answers one question only about baseline stability. The cost is that this round may not improve frontier numerically, but establishing a repeatable anchor is higher-value than immediately touching LR after only one winning run on a freshly promoted family.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0176.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, with the only architectural change versus the mainline being a fixed front-loaded sparse budget split (`stage1_k≈0.75K`, `stage2_k≈0.25K`). This is `扩展兼容` because LUTurbo can export the low-rank trunk, soft codebook, and residual dictionary as static libraries and execute them in the usual `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two residual lookups + weighted sum` pipeline. Because this family keeps the same trunk/codebook/residual components as the mainline and only reallocates K across the two residual stages, its encoder selection cost should remain within the same feasible regime as the current mainline rather than triggering policy rejection. The probe answers one question only: at low-cost EF=2, is front-loading the residual budget intrinsically better than the symmetric two-stage split, or should this family be deprioritized.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune a single cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If the asymmetric probe underperforms or slows training without clear FVU benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: export path is identical to the mainline soft-codebook two-stage family; only stage budget allocation changes.","This is the cleanest remaining matched architecture probe because it preserves the mainline's static libraries and likely feasible encoder cost, avoiding another likely policy-reject like routed/bucketed variants.","When reviewing the run, check not just FVU but also `tokens_per_sec`, total runtime, and `final_total_tokens` to see whether any gain is offset by slower training."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` stay fixed. I am avoiding another clearly over-budget probe and choosing a matched variant that isolates one architectural question while remaining compatible with LUTurbo export and likely feasible under the selection-cost constraint.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as the one matched architecture change against the current mainline recipe. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`), keeps the same static trunk/codebook/residual libraries, and tests whether a front-loaded two-stage residual budget is worth continuing in the low-EF feasible regime.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 17 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=24` still descended smoothly through the late phase rather than flattening early, so the current recipe appears capacity-limited but still stable. This round changes only `K`, moving from `24` to `16`, to answer whether LUTurbo can reach the next allowed lower-cost point before reconstruction degradation becomes clearly impractical.","summary":"Continue the active topk low-K frontier mapping: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the deployable cost-quality frontier extends one more step down.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` mainline, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` and allowed-K constraints, and follows directly from the observed curve shape at `K=24`. The main risk is a steeper quality drop and higher dead-feature pressure at `K=16`, but `K=24` still showed smooth late improvement, so the next informative single question is whether the frontier boundary is at `K=16` or below `K=24`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 (`K=24`) reached `FVU=0.2722620368003845`, a modest degradation from `K=32`, and its late-phase slope remained negative instead of collapsing into an early plateau.","Compared with `K=32`, the `K=24` run showed higher `dead_pct` and `auxk` pressure in the late phase, suggesting capacity is getting tight, but the training dynamics still looked stable enough to justify one more K-only step.","For LUTurbo, this is still the most direct way to probe lower online selection and weighted-sum cost while staying within the same export-compatible topk recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16` remains reasonably close to `K=24`, continue once more to `K=8` to locate the true lower boundary of the current recipe.","If `K=16` degrades sharply or late-phase improvement largely disappears, treat `K=24` or `K=32` as the practical low-K boundary for this topk/signum regime.","If `K=16` is borderline, compare it against `K=24` as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 56 answered the loss question on the strengthened `gated` recipe cleanly enough: removing the auxiliary term finished essentially flat-to-worse (`0.142968` vs the `0.142923` anchor), so the mainline recipe remains `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. With LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess now all re-checked on the active family, the next single question in the prescribed order is back on the K axis: if we keep the finalized `gated` recipe fixed and reduce only `K` from `128` to `96`, does the lower-cost point still reproduce a healthy full training curve under the now-settled mainline recipe, or was the earlier `K=96` result partly specific to an intermediate recipe-validation phase?",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_cost",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:25:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `k`. It also follows the required sequencing: the mainline recipe has now been re-localized on LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess, so returning to K is the clean next step. The main risk is spending a round on confirmation rather than frontier expansion, but after four consecutive non-improving recipe probes the most useful next question is whether the first lower-cost operating point is stable under the finalized recipe rather than only under the earlier sweep context.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:83:      "If the refreshed `gated@96` run reproduces a healthy curve near or better than the existing `0.160940` point, treat the lower-cost frontier as stable and continue down the K ladder only if a further deployment question remains.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the now-settled mainline recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `128` to `96` to refresh the first lower-cost deployment point under the finalized recipe. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: if the curve remains smooth and lands near or below the current `gated@96` frontier (`0.160940`), then the strengthened recipe is stable enough to treat that lower-cost point as a reliable LUTurbo candidate; if it degrades materially, re-open the question of whether the prior K sweep depended on transient recipe-state rather than the settled mainline.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0057.json:105:    "self_review": "This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `k`. It also follows the required sequencing: the mainline recipe has now been re-localized on LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess, so returning to K is the clean next step. The main risk is spending a round on confirmation rather than frontier expansion, but after four consecutive non-improving recipe probes the most useful next question is whether the first lower-cost operating point is stable under the finalized recipe rather than only under the earlier sweep context.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0143.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 architecture \u7684\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u662f\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5b57\u5178\u5e93\u4e0a\u7684\u56fa\u5b9a\u5411\u91cf\uff0calpha_i \u4e3a\u9009\u51fa\u7684\u7a00\u758f\u7cfb\u6570\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff1b\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u4e0e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual \u76f8\u6bd4\uff0cfactorized_topk \u4e0d\u518d\u4f7f\u7528 trunk\u3001soft codebook \u6216\u4e24\u9636\u6bb5 refinement\uff0c\u800c\u662f\u7528\u4f4e\u79e9 scorer \u505a\u5355\u5e93\u7a00\u758f\u9009\u62e9\uff0c\u4ecd\u4fdd\u6301\u9759\u6001\u5e93\u6709\u9650\u52a0\u6743\u548c\u7684\u90e8\u7f72\u5f62\u5f0f\uff1b\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b\u5176 encoder selection_cost \u7ea6 0.38x h\u00d7n\uff0c\u663e\u8457\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u4e3b\u7ebf\u7684\u7ea6 1.25x\uff0c\u6ee1\u8db3 \u22641.5x \u786c\u7ea6\u675f\uff0c\u90e8\u7f72\u4fa7\u4e5f\u53ea\u9700\u5355\u5e93 sparse lookup\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u53ea\u56de\u7b54\u4e00\u4e2a matched architecture probe \u95ee\u9898\uff1a\u5728 K=128\u3001EF=2\u3001signum\u3001LR=3.0e-3 \u5b8c\u5168\u4e0d\u53d8\u65f6\uff0c\u8fd9\u79cd\u66f4\u6fc0\u8fdb\u7684\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\uff0c\u8fd8\u662f\u5b83\u5728\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF regime \u4e0b\u4f1a\u56e0\u8868\u793a\u80fd\u529b\u4e0d\u8db3\u800c\u660e\u663e\u843d\u540e\u4e8e\u73b0\u6709 soft-codebook/two-stage \u4e3b\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0143.json:22:    "expected_win": "lower_cost",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0143.json:25:    "self_review": "\u9075\u5b88\u5355\u53d8\u91cf\u539f\u5219\u4e0e\u672c\u8f6e probe \u7ea6\u675f\uff1a\u53ea\u6539 architecture\uff0c\u672a\u8054\u52a8 K\u3001EF\u3001optimizer\u3001LR \u6216\u5176\u4ed6 recipe\u3002\u9009\u62e9 factorized_topk\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u5b83\u5728 EF=2 \u4e0b selection_cost \u660e\u663e\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5f53\u524d\u6240\u6709\u517c\u5bb9 frontier \u70b9\uff0c\u4e14\u5c5e\u4e8e\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u9759\u6001\u8868\u793a\uff0c\u80fd\u76f4\u63a5\u56de\u7b54\u201c\u66f4\u6fc0\u8fdb\u7684\u4f4e\u79e9\u5355\u5e93\u9009\u62e9\u673a\u5236\u662f\u5426\u503c\u5f97\u7ee7\u7eed\u201d\u8fd9\u4e00\u72ec\u7acb\u67b6\u6784\u95ee\u9898\u3002\u98ce\u9669\u662f\u8be5 family \u5728\u65e7\u7684\u9ad8 EF regime \u66fe\u660e\u663e\u504f\u5f31\uff0c\u4f46\u5f53\u524d\u4f4e EF \u6210\u672c\u7ea6\u675f\u5df2\u53d1\u751f regime shift\uff0c\u8fd9\u6b63\u662f\u672c\u8f6e probe \u7684\u4fe1\u606f\u4ef7\u503c\u6240\u5728\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0143.json:53:      "\u8bc4\u4f30\u65f6\u5fc5\u987b\u540c\u65f6\u6bd4\u8f83 FVU\u3001selection_cost\u3001deploy cost\u3001tokens_per_sec\u3001\u603b\u8017\u65f6\u548c final_total_tokens\uff0c\u907f\u514d\u53ea\u6309\u7ec8\u70b9 SAE \u6307\u6807\u5224\u65ad\u67b6\u6784\u4ef7\u503c\u3002"
