research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0059.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the matched `topk` probe came back only slightly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, the next highest-value single architecture question is whether a simpler export-compatible scoring path can retain most of the quality while offering a cheaper route for online selection and coefficient computation. `factorized_topk` keeps the same static-dictionary finite weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk/gated`, but replaces direct latent scoring with a low-rank mixing stage before top-k selection, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `factorized_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a LUTurbo-oriented family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 59 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `factorized_topk` is a stronger LUTurbo-oriented probe than opening another heavier residual family because it preserves the same export contract while plausibly reducing support-scoring complexity; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe understates its ceiling, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 showed that matched `topk` under the strengthened `gated` recipe is only modestly worse (`0.146999` vs `0.142923`), so simpler export-compatible architectures remain worth probing when the `gated` mainline stalls.","`factorized_topk` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to a low-rank scoring stage before top-k support selection.","Round 59 should judge `factorized_topk` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `factorized_topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `factorized_topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its scoring path may align better with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `factorized_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0178.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and the gated selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and with what coefficients. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then run `trunk branch + gated sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The architectural question is whether dropping the soft-codebook branch but using a gated residual selector yields a better low-cost tradeoff than the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. Selection cost should remain within the feasible regime at `EF=2`, so this probe should produce a real training signal rather than another fast policy reject.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0178.json:25:    "self_review": "Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, with `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe is intentionally chosen to answer a clean architectural question inside the feasible cost band instead of spending another round on an architecture that is likely to be policy-rejected immediately.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0178.json:52:      "This is a useful matched probe because it is likely budget-feasible at `EF=2`, unlike routed/bucketed two-stage variants, and it tests whether the soft-codebook branch is actually necessary in the current low-cost regime.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0178.json:56:      "Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0178.json:78:    "self_review": "Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, with `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe is intentionally chosen to answer a clean architectural question inside the feasible cost band instead of spending another round on an architecture that is likely to be policy-rejected immediately.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0168.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_gated_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + \u03a3_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary; the gate only changes how residual coefficients are selected, not the exported decoder basis. This is `\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one static trunk lookup plus one sparse weighted sum over a static residual vector library, with the gate absorbed entirely into online coefficient/selection logic. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost stays within the `\u2264 1.5\u00d7h\u00d7n` hard budget and remains below the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether this simpler low-rank gated selector is intrinsically strong enough in the current low-EF deployable regime to justify any later follow-up, or whether the mainline\u2019s soft-codebook plus second stage is clearly necessary.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0168.json:25:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0168.json:57:      "If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, record it as a lower-cost compatible side branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0168.json:58:      "If it is unexpectedly close to the mainline at lower selection cost, schedule at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0168.json:79:    "self_review": "This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields that caused recent policy confusion. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the highest-value remaining matched probe because it preserves LUTurbo exportability, stays within the EF=2 selection-cost budget, and tests whether a simpler one-stage low-rank selector can recover more quality than plain `lowrank_residual` without paying the full mainline cost. The main risk is that the added gate branch may not close enough of the FVU gap to justify even its moderate extra runtime.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0182.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"128"}],"expected_win":"pareto_improve","experiment_tier":"mainline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","hypothesis":"Mainline cost-reduction step on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` with only `NUM_CODES` changed from the implicit default to `128`. Final reconstruction remains `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, so this family is still `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the low-rank trunk library, the static codebook library `C`, and the static residual dictionary `B`, then run `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two sparse residual lookups + weighted sum` online. This round asks one question only: can a smaller coarse codebook preserve most of the EF=2 mainline quality while reducing both encoder selection cost and deployment lookup cost enough to improve the Pareto point. Reducing `NUM_CODES` directly shrinks `code_router`, `codebook_matmul`, and `codebook_deploy`, making it a cleaner first cost knob than changing multiple recipe terms at once.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `NUM_CODES=128` holds FVU close to the current mainline while reducing cost, continue along the same axis with a smaller codebook or then test `TRUNK_RANK` as the next single cost knob.","If FVU degrades sharply, revert to the current mainline codebook size and try `TRUNK_RANK` instead as the next mainline cost-reduction variable."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` remains LUTurbo `扩展兼容` under `NUM_CODES=128`; only the size of the static coarse codebook changes, not the export path.","This round isolates the coarse-codebook-size question and should reduce both selection cost and deployment cost simultaneously, unlike `STAGE1_RATIO` which mostly reallocates sparse budget without shrinking static lookup structures.","Review `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU to confirm whether any improvement comes from true efficiency rather than a shorter or cheaper run artifact."],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: the family and main recipe stay fixed, and only `NUM_CODES` changes. This follows the stated mainline priority order by keeping EF in-budget and then applying a direct cost knob that can improve both selector cost and LUTurbo deployment cost without introducing a new architecture.","summary":"Push the mainline family forward by shrinking the coarse codebook to `NUM_CODES=128` while keeping `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, and `lr=3e-3` fixed. This is a clean Pareto test for whether the current two-stage soft-codebook architecture can trade a smaller static coarse library for lower total LUTurbo cost without giving up too much reconstruction quality.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0022.json:17:    "hypothesis": "Round 21 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=96` is a promising high-quality reduced-cost point: its curve kept descending smoothly through the late phase, and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` stayed very low. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis, lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping the `K=96` recipe fixed, to answer whether the new near-anchor deployment point is slightly over-regularized and can recover a bit more reconstruction quality without destabilizing training.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0022.json:18:    "summary": "Run a single loss-axis test on the newly validated `K=96` topk point: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `K=96`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to see whether weaker auxiliary pressure improves the high-quality reduced-cost recipe.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0022.json:23:    "self_review": "This stays on the active `topk` family, changes exactly one primary variable (`other_param` via `AUXK_ALPHA`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed `K=96` curve shape. The main risk is that the gain may be small, but `K=96` is now the most promising reduced-cost point and its very low dead-feature pressure makes a clean over-regularization check more justified than continuing to remap K.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0022.json:53:      "Round 21 established `K=96` as a strong high-quality reduced-cost point: late-phase FVU kept descending smoothly and both `dead_pct` and `auxk` remained near zero.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0022.json:60:      "If reducing `AUXK_ALPHA` hurts stability or quality, the current auxiliary pressure is likely already appropriate for this near-anchor reduced-cost point."
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0205.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"smaller_k","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；factorized scorer 仅用于在线打分与选址，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。基于 r204 已在 K=64、EF=2 下拿到 0.44x / 0.3013 的 <0.5x 点，本轮继续保持 architecture、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，仅将 K 从 64 下探到 32，预计 deployment cost 可由约 0.06x 进一步降到约 0.03x，使 total_cost 约落在 0.41x，补全更低成本端覆盖，并检验该 family 在更短查表链路下的 FVU 退化斜率。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=32 仍保持可接受 FVU，可继续在 factorized_topk 上单变量下探 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM，争取把 encoder cost 也往下压。","如果 K=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则保留 K=64 作为 <0.5x 主点，并转去 topk 或 lowrank_residual 的低成本对照以补前沿形状。"],"notes_to_memory":["factorized_topk 在 LUTurbo 链路中可直接导出为单静态字典的 top-k 查表加权和，兼容性稳定，不因 scorer factorization 改变 decoder 形式。","本轮继续只改 K，沿 deployment 成本轴下探，避免把 encoder 降本与 lookup 降本混在一起。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，目标明确指向 <0.5x 区域扩点。主要风险是 K=32 可能把 FVU 推高过快，但这正是当前低开销 regime 需要量化的 tradeoff。","summary":"在直接兼容 family factorized_topk 上做单变量低开销下探：固定 EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 K 从 64 降到 32，目标是把 total_cost 从 0.44x 进一步压到约 0.41x，并补全 <0.5x Pareto 前沿的更低部署成本端。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0129.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 low-rank trunk 向量库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、residual 字典库 {b_i} 均为静态可导出向量库，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前该 family 在 EF=2 时 selection_cost 约 1.25x，已在 ≤1.5x 预算内；因此本轮只测试学习率这一主变量，检验把 LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3 是否能改善 late-training 收敛形状并在不增加选择成本、不改变部署查表成本的前提下降低 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 2.4e-3 曲线更稳但最终仍略高，可继续在同 family/EF=2/K=128 上做更细 LR 下扫（如 2.0e-3）。","若 2.4e-3 明显变慢或欠收敛，则回到 3.0e-3，并把下一轮主变量切到 optimizer（如在固定 family/EF/K 下测试 Adam 配套重调 LR）。","若 LR 调整无收益，再考虑 clean baseline 复验吞吐与总耗时是否因 recipe 漂移而恶化。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出路径已明确：trunk、codebook、两阶段 residual 都可表示为静态向量库上的有限加权和，family 维持扩展兼容。","当前主线 family 在 EF=2 下满足 selection_cost 硬约束；本轮不改 K，避免把部署查表成本与学习率效应混杂。","本轮单变量为 LR，仅用于判断现有 feasible 主线是否存在更优收敛点。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则，只改 LR。未新开 family，未触碰执行层，也未引入超过预算的选择成本风险。风险是 LR 下调可能主要带来更慢收敛而非更低终点，需要结合 tokens_per_sec、总耗时和曲线形状一起判读。","summary":"在已满足成本预算的 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线上做一次纯学习率下调复验：固定 ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、OPTIMIZER=signum，仅把 LR 从 3.0e-3 调到 2.4e-3，目标是在不改变 LUTurbo 导出形式和在线成本的前提下改善收敛并争取刷新可行 frontier。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0051.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At the current lower-K anchor (`K=40`) and fair small-capacity setting (`EF=8`), `lowrank_gated_residual` may be undertrained rather than fundamentally weak; dropping the learning rate from `1.6e-3` to `4e-4` while keeping the rest of the recipe fixed is the narrowest exploitation-mode check for whether this family can recover a competitive small-EF proxy point without reopening architecture or EF.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization sweep on `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8`, `signum`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0`, changing only `LR` to `4e-4` to test whether the recent weak fair-comparison result was a step-size mismatch rather than a true quality ceiling.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the runtime exploitation guidance, keeps the single primary variable to LR, respects the EF<=16 / prefer-EF=8 constraint, and continues lower-K work instead of drifting back to EF=32. The main risk is that the family is simply too weak at `K=40, EF=8`, but this is still the least-cost informative check before moving to the next prescribed sweep point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Exploitation-mode follow-up: keep `lowrank_gated_residual` fixed at the fair small-capacity comparison point (`K=40`, `EF=8`) and sweep LR downward before concluding the family is weak there.","This round changes only LR; architecture, K, EF, optimizer, and aux regularization stay fixed to isolate whether the weak `EF=8` result was a step-size issue."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` materially improves `K=40, EF=8`, test the remaining untried lower LR (`2e-4`) at the same setting to map the small-EF stability window.","If `LR=4e-4` is still clearly weak, keep the family fixed and move to the next prescribed capacity-efficiency probe at small EF (prefer `EF=12` before any larger EF)."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0213.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算系数 beta_r 与 alpha_i，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时可拆成 trunk 库查表加权和与 residual 库查表加权和，两部分都满足静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此兼容性为扩展兼容。基于 r210 已在当前 family 上拿到 0.69x / 0.1256 且 tokens_per_sec 约 166.6k、总耗时 291s，当前最值得回答的单一问题不是再换 family，而是该点的高成本是否主要由 trunk 过宽导致；本轮仅将 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 16，测试能否在保持明显优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU 前提下，把 total_cost 尽量压向并最好压入 <0.5x 区域。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 进入 <0.5x 且 FVU 仍明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则固定该 family 后只沿 K 轴补一个点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 的 FVU 明显崩塌或训练代价没有进一步优势，则说明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低开销区仍过度依赖 trunk 容量，后续应回到更短链路 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["r210 说明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低 EF 下具备很强质量潜力，且运行吞吐优于近期 topk 线；当前主要矛盾是成本而非训练不稳。","TRUNK_RANK 同时影响 encoder 与 deployment 两侧成本，是把该 family 从 0.69x 拉回低开销区的最高信息量单变量旋钮。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"这轮严格只改一个主变量 trunk_rank，不再重复声明 K、EF、optimizer、LR，避免再次触发 param_only 的多主轴拒绝。选择 16 而不是 32，是因为目标是优先补 <0.5x 区域覆盖；更激进地下压 trunk 才更可能一次性把该高质量点推进到低开销前沿，但风险是 coarse trunk 表达会被过度削弱。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上做一次低开销 param-only 探索：仅将 TRUNK_RANK 设为 16，验证能否以更小 trunk 库把当前 0.69x/0.1256 的高质量点推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0223.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"LR","value":"3.6e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，部署侧仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。r222 已证明在 `topk@EF1,K248` 上去掉 auxiliary-K loss 与 r218 基本等价，说明当前 <0.5x 最强锚点的 loss 轴已没有明确收益；因此下一步应按开放假设转向同一锚点上的单变量 LR probe。基于低成本 signum 主线上历史上“2.4e-3 -> 3.0e-3` 往往优于向下回退，而当前 `topk@EF1,K248` 曲线仍显示 late-stage 仍在缓降，本轮严格锚定有效参考轮 r222，仅把 `LR` 从 `3.0e-3` 上调到 `3.6e-3`，测试更积极的步长能否在不改变 total_cost 的前提下，把 <0.5x 区域最佳 FVU 从 0.1462 再向下压，同时检查是否会像历史高 LR probe 一样带来吞吐下降或总时长恶化。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `LR=3.6e-3` 在保持接近当前吞吐与总 token 的同时把 FVU 压到 0.1462 以下，则下一轮对该更高 LR 配方做一次 clean repeat，确认它是新的低成本 topk 锚点。","如果 `LR=3.6e-3` 与 `3.0e-3` 基本等价但运行代价更差，则关闭 topk 主线的向上 LR 分支，并把 topk recipe 空间暂时视为已基本饱和。","如果 `LR=3.6e-3` 明显退化或显著拖慢训练，则恢复 `LR=3.0e-3` 作为 topk 低成本锚点，下一轮转向新的低成本 family 而不是继续在 topk 上做 recipe 试探。"],"notes_to_memory":["r222 表明在 `topk@EF1,K248` 低成本主线上，`AUXK_ALPHA` 不是关键因子；后续应优先检查 LR 或转向新 family，而不是继续做 loss 轴清洗。","本轮不改变 decoder 端导出形态，也不改变 selection/deployment 成本；它只回答当前最强 <0.5x 锚点是否还存在纯优化层面的剩余空间。","评估本轮时必须同时比较 FVU、tokens_per_sec、duration_sec 与 final_total_tokens；若只有极小 FVU 收益但训练明显更慢，应视为负面信号。"],"reference_round":222,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效 reference r222 只改 `LR`，family、K、EF、optimizer、AUXK_ALPHA` 及所有结构参数保持不变。选择向上探到 `3.6e-3` 而不是先下探，是因为当前低成本 signum 主线的已知证据更支持“较大步长可能还有收益”，而不是立即回退到更保守设置；主要风险是更高 LR 可能带来与历史相似的运行时恶化，因此必须把系统代价与终点质量一起判读。","summary":"相对 r222 的 `topk@EF1,K248,AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 做一次严格 param_only LR probe，仅把 `LR` 上调到 `3.6e-3`，验证当前最强 <0.5x 低成本锚点是否还能通过更积极的 signum 步长进一步压低 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
