research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0204.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"smaller_k","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库，低秩 factor scorer 只参与在线选择、不改变 decoder 形式，因此对 LUTurbo/Lottable 属于直接兼容。单主变量选择 k：把当前 0.50x 前沿点 factorized_topk 从 K=128 下调到 K=64，保持 ARCHITECTURE/EF/OPT/LR 不变，可把 deployment cost 约从 0.12x 降到 0.06x，使 total_cost 约从 0.50x 降到 0.44x，直接补到 <0.5x 区域；预期 FVU 会升高，但仍可能成为该低开销区域的首个有效 Pareto 点。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=64 成功占住 <0.5x 前沿，再继续沿同一 family 单变量下探 K=32。","如果 K=64 的 FVU 退化过大，再回到 factorized_topk 固定 K=64，单变量下调 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM 以继续压 encoder 成本，或转向 topk/EF=1 做更低成本锚点。"],"notes_to_memory":["factorized_topk 的 decoder 仍是单静态字典加权和，属于直接兼容 family，可继续作为 <0.5x 区域主力低成本基线。","本轮只改 K，避免把 architecture/EF/LR 混入，便于归因低开销前沿是否主要受 lookup 成本驱动。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"方案严格遵守单变量原则，且不需要改 sparsify/ 代码。主要风险是 K=64 的 FVU 可能明显差于现有 0.50x 点；但当前任务优先级是补 <0.5x 覆盖，这个风险是可接受的。","summary":"运行一个纯参数低开销探索：保持 factorized_topk, EF=2, signum, LR=3e-3 不变，仅将 K 从 128 降到 64，目标是在直接兼容前提下把 total_cost 压到约 0.44x，并为 <0.5x 区域建立首个可行 Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0245.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"frontier_mapping","hypothesis":"候选 family: group_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；group_topk 只改变单样本在线侧的支持形成方式：先在每个静态分组内选 winner，再做全局 top-k 保留，但 decoder 端仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 reference_round=r242 只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE=group_topk`，保持 `K=96`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`OPTIMIZER=signum`、`LR=0.003` 及其余配置不变，测试在约 0.34x 总成本位置，用更均匀的组内竞争是否能比 `topk@K96` 的 FVU=0.2219 给出更好的低开销 Pareto 权衡，同时避免继续拉长 plain topk 的查表链路。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `group_topk@K96` 明显优于 `topk@K96`，且 `tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens` 没有明显恶化，则下一轮继续相对本轮单变量上探 `K=128`，判断 grouped support 在中低成本区是否形成一条独立前沿。","如果 `group_topk@K96` 与 `topk@K96` 基本持平但运行更慢，则关闭 grouped support 这条低成本支线，不再把它作为 `<0.5x` 区域默认优先方向。","如果 `group_topk@K96` 明显差于 `topk@K96`，则说明在当前低开销 regime 下，单库 support reallocation 本身不足以超过 plain topk；后续应转向其他 family，而不是继续在 group 规则上加密。"],"notes_to_memory":["r242 显示 plain `topk@K96` 虽把 FVU 压到 0.2219，但总时长升到 508s，继续沿 plain topk 的 K 轴细扫已出现负面系统信号。","r243 的 `jumprelu@K96` 和 r244 的 `factorized_topk@K96` 都未能击败 `topk@K96`，因此下一步更高信息量的问题是：在同一 0.34x 成本槽位，仅改变 support allocation 规则是否还有收益。","本轮评估必须同时比较 `val_fvu`、`tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens`；若只是微小质量变化但运行更慢，应直接记为负信号。"],"reference_round":242,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r242 只改 `ARCHITECTURE`，不联动 K、EF、optimizer、LR 或任何 group 专属参数。选择 `group_topk` 而不是继续加密 topk、jump 或 factorized scorer，是因为前两条新支线已经给出负信号，而 group_topk 保持与 topk 同阶的部署成本和同一导出契约，能在当前 `<0.5x` 主战区提供一个更可解释的 support-allocation 探针。","summary":"严格锚定 r242，仅切到 `group_topk`，在约 0.34x 总成本位置测试分组竞争的单库结构能否比 `topk@K96` 给出更好的 cost-FVU 权衡，同时检查它是否比近期失败的 jump/factorized 分支更值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0061.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 60 showed that matched `jumprelu` is competitive enough to avoid immediate dismissal but still clearly trails the strengthened `gated` anchor (`0.148243` vs `0.142923`), so the next single architecture question should test the closest support-selection near-neighbor rather than another looser variant. `routed` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum reconstruction contract while separating support routing from activation magnitude, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `routed` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a deployment-relevant family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `routed`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `routed`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `routed` stays smooth and lands near the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because decoupled routing may offer a better LUTurbo cost/quality tradeoff than full gating; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 61 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `routed` is the highest-value remaining probe because it stays very close to the successful `gated` family while changing only the support-selection mechanism, which is directly relevant to LUTurbo online cost. The main risk is that the matched `gated`-tuned recipe may not be ideal for routed support, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 60 showed that matched `jumprelu` is only modestly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor (`0.148243` vs `0.142923`), so simpler support-shaping variants are still worth probing when mainline progress stalls.","`routed` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to using a separate router for support selection while preserving the same export form.","Round 61 should judge `routed` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `routed` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `routed` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because decoupled routing may better align with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `routed` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
