research/history_archive/05_20260320_181635/memory.json:2:  "current_focus": "Treat K=128 only as the initial search anchor, not as a success criterion. The research objective is to find configurations whose FVU is dramatically better than the current K=128 baseline, with a target on the order of halving that baseline FVU before rewarding smaller K or lower cost.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed at the latest executed point `K=1` and reducing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 12 to 8 will test whether this family can deliver a strictly cheaper ultra-low-K point with acceptable additional FVU.","summary":"Use a parameter-only probe on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=1`, changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` to `8` while pinning `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This repairs the prior isolation failure by holding `K` at the last successful run and probing the remaining frontier dimension cleanly.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_ef","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the cleanest recovery after the policy rejection: it changes exactly one experimental dimension relative to the last real run, preserves the current family, and probes whether the ultra-low-K endpoint can also become cheaper.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"1"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 10 recovers from the prior policy rejection by holding `K` at the latest successful point (`K=1`) and changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR`.","When the controller enforces strict isolation against the latest executed run, EF sweeps should start from the most recent successful K rather than jumping back to an older anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=1, EF=8` stays competitive, continue the EF sweep at the same `K=1` to `EF=6` to find the cost-quality floor.","If `K=1, EF=8` degrades too much, keep `EF=12` as the ultra-low-K recipe and try an EF sweep later from the `K=2` or `K=4` lane with strict sequential isolation.","If `K=1, EF=8` is borderline but promising, test `EF=10` at the same `K=1` to refine the knee."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
