research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0135.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After three non-improving rounds, the cleanest exploitation move is to tune the current smallest exposed bucketed frontier point rather than perturb higher-K anchors. Reducing the learning rate from `3.2e-3` to the untested `1.6e-3` may stabilize optimization for `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32, EF=16` and recover lower FVU without changing sparsity cost.","summary":"Run a pure learning-rate sweep on the current `K=32` bucketed frontier recipe by keeping architecture, expansion factor, optimizer, and aux fixed while changing only `LR` to `1.6e-3`. This follows the stagnation guidance to exploit the current best family and prioritizes the more valuable smaller-K tradeoff point over higher-K anchors.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the most policy-compliant exploitation step: one variable only, no new architecture, EF fixed at 16, and focused on the highest-value smaller-K frontier slot. I chose LR before aux because the recent failures suggest recipe sensitivity, and `1.6e-3` is the closest untested value to the successful `3.2e-3` baseline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 135 enters explicit exploitation mode on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` after three consecutive no-improve rounds.","Prioritize the `K=32` frontier slot because improving the smallest exposed non-dominated point is more valuable than tuning the already-strong K64/K96/K128 anchors.","Keep the recipe fixed to `signum` and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so this round isolates LR alone under the operator-mandated `EF=16` regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves the K32 bucketed point, continue the same exploitation lane with one untested `AUXK_ALPHA` value on that improved recipe.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is neutral or worse, test the next untested LR on the same K32 bucketed recipe before leaving exploitation mode.","If the LR reduction materially worsens convergence, treat the bucketed K32 recipe as preferring the higher-LR regime and pivot to an aux-only sweep instead of more optimizer changes."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0010.json:74:    "expected_win": "cost",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"On the updated best anchor `lowrank_two_stage_residual, K=32, EF=12, LR=3.2e-3`, introducing a small auxiliary loss with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` may improve feature utilization enough to reduce FVU further without changing sparsity cost.","summary":"Run an isolated aux sweep on the new best `K=32` recipe, holding architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and LR fixed while changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.0` to `0.01`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the current exploitation lane cleanly: only one parameter changes from the latest successful run, and the test stays on the strongest anchor rather than broadening search. After finding a better LR, the highest-information next step is a small aux value rather than another large recipe change.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 should exploit the improved `K=32, EF=12` anchor by testing a small nonzero `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` with all other fields pinned to the new best recipe.","This probes whether the stronger `LR=3.2e-3` optimization setting changes the aux tradeoff relative to the earlier low-K failures, which may have been regime-specific rather than family-wide."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` improves the `K=32` anchor, try `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` next on the same fixed recipe to map the local optimum.","If it is neutral or worse, revert to `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` for the high-quality anchor and consider the remaining LR sweep point only if more confirmation is needed.","If the gain is small but real, keep the new aux setting on the `K=32` anchor and then test whether the same setting transfers to a smaller-K frontier point."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0096.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has now improved the frontier at `K=64`, so the next highest-value measurement is `K=96`, which can reveal whether the same architecture continues the Pareto curve at a lower cost than `K=128` while preserving most of the quality gain.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=96` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This extends the current winning recipe to the next allowed anchor and prioritizes a potentially non-dominated smaller-K tradeoff before jumping straight to `K=128`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is the cleanest next step because only `K` changes and the family is already showing consistent gains from `K=16` through `K=64`. Choosing `K=96` before `K=128` matches the stated objective that smaller K is valuable when it creates a non-dominated tradeoff. The main risk is that quality may flatten only at `K=128`, but mapping `K=96` first is the better Pareto decision.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["r96 should extend `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to `K=96` after the family established a new `K=64` frontier point.","Prefer `K=96` before `K=128` because a smaller-K non-dominated point is more valuable than immediately chasing the highest-K anchor.","Keep the recipe fixed and change only `K` to cleanly measure whether the routed soft-codebook advantage persists into the upper-K regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=96`, test the same family at `K=128` to complete the high-K map.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=96`, consider one confirmatory run at `K=128` before deciding whether the family saturates in the upper-K regime.","If it clearly loses at `K=96`, conclude that the routed soft-codebook advantage peaks around `K=64` and shift future high-K work to a different architecture or recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:19:    "hypothesis": "The optimizer and aux-loss stages did not improve on the `topk` signum anchor, so the next mainline question is whether a slightly smaller support can preserve most of the reconstruction while improving LUTurbo deployment cost. Reducing `K` from `128` to `96` is the least aggressive first step on the K axis and should reveal whether the current topk recipe has obvious over-allocation in support size.",
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:20:    "summary": "Keep the `topk` mainline recipe fixed at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the original auxiliary setting, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. This starts the K stage with the nearest lower allowed value, so the run cleanly answers whether LUTurbo can gain a cost-friendly support reduction before quality drops sharply.",
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:25:    "self_review": "This follows the prescribed order: LR and optimizer were explored, the aux-loss probe did not improve the frontier, and now the search moves to K. The main risk is that `K=96` may be too close to `K=128` to unlock a meaningful deployment gain, but it is still the most interpretable first K move and gives a clean slope estimate for the cost-quality tradeoff.",
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:69:      "Round 7 begins K exploration with the smallest possible move from the anchor, `K=96`, to estimate the local cost-quality slope before taking larger support cuts."
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:72:      "If `K=96` stays close to the `K=128` anchor with a healthy curve, continue down to `K=64` on the same recipe to look for a real LUTurbo cost win.",
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:94:    "description": "Keep the `topk` mainline recipe fixed at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the original auxiliary setting, and change only `K` from `128` to `96`. This starts the K stage with the nearest lower allowed value, so the run cleanly answers whether LUTurbo can gain a cost-friendly support reduction before quality drops sharply.",
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0007.json:95:    "self_review": "This follows the prescribed order: LR and optimizer were explored, the aux-loss probe did not improve the frontier, and now the search moves to K. The main risk is that `K=96` may be too close to `K=128` to unlock a meaningful deployment gain, but it is still the most interpretable first K move and gives a clean slope estimate for the cost-quality tradeoff.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At the ultra-low-K anchor, increasing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from the baseline to `0.03125` for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=1, EF=12` may improve feature usage enough to reduce FVU without changing sparsity cost, potentially strengthening the frontier endpoint.","summary":"Run a strictly single-variable follow-up from the latest successful ultra-low-K recipe by keeping architecture, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed and changing only `AUXK_ALPHA`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This avoids the recent isolation failures by staying on the current family and current K/EF anchor and changing only one scalar hyperparameter. It does not introduce code edits, architecture changes, or coupled K/EF moves.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"1"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 12 should recover from repeated isolation rejects by holding the latest successful `lowrank_two_stage_residual` ultra-low-K recipe fixed at `K=1, EF=12` and varying only `AUXK_ALPHA`.","This tests whether auxiliary feature encouragement can improve the `K=1` endpoint without altering sparsity cost or architecture, which is directly relevant to strengthening the Pareto frontier tail."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` improves `K=1`, test the same single-variable change at `K=2` to check whether the ultra-low-K tail consistently benefits.","If it hurts or is neutral at `K=1`, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` as the ultra-low-K default and shift the next round to another isolated scalar on the same anchor.","If the gain is meaningful, consider a small `AUXK_ALPHA` refinement at the same anchor before changing family or EF."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0015.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"On the current best frontier point `lowrank_two_stage_residual, K=32, EF=12`, decreasing only the learning rate from `1.6e-3` to `4e-4` may improve optimization stability enough to lower FVU and strengthen the quality anchor without changing sparsity cost.","summary":"Run an exploitation follow-up on the current best recipe by holding architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and `AUXK_ALPHA` fixed and changing only `LR` to an untested lower value.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the exploitation guidance exactly: no new architecture, no EF move, and one parameter changed on the current best frontier recipe. I chose an untested LR sweep point rather than another aux sweep because aux already looked harmful in the low-K regime, while LR tuning is the cleanest remaining lever on the strongest anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 15 enters exploitation mode on the current best `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor at `K=32, EF=12` and changes only `LR` to `4e-4`.","This tests whether the best-FVU point is slightly optimization-limited and can be improved by a more conservative signum step size without changing sparsity or architecture."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` improves the `K=32` anchor, continue the LR sweep on the same fixed recipe with another untested value before touching aux.","If it underperforms clearly, try the opposite LR direction (`3.2e-3`) on the same anchor as the next isolated exploitation round.","If LR tuning shows low sensitivity, move to a small aux sweep on the same `K=32, EF=12` anchor with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` while keeping all else fixed."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
