research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:131:{"event_id": "evt_1774030420638497565", "ts": 1774030420, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 10, "session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "mainline_comparison", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "cost", "hypothesis": "JumpReLU may still deliver a usable smaller-K regime at K=32, and measuring that directly is the highest-value next step now that K=64 stayed stable enough to earn a full run."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:208:{"event_id": "evt_1774031436135419778", "ts": 1774031436, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 14, "session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0c67-c69b-7611-b10d-8445e011f41d", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "jumprelu", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "quality", "hypothesis": "JumpReLU at K=128 may be paying unnecessary reconstruction cost to the auxiliary dead-feature objective, and removing auxk pressure could lower primary FVU below the current 0.1724 full frontier."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:446:{"event_id": "evt_1774060313705784597", "ts": 1774060313, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 32, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "group_topk", "family_stage": "prototype", "change_type": "edit_sae_code", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:537:{"event_id": "evt_1774061974833512932", "ts": 1774061974, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 37, "session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d0e3a-6671-7002-9230-abf599a6f50f", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "pareto", "hypothesis": "Now that gated holds the full frontier at K=128, K=64, and K=32, the next informative move is to test whether the low-K regime is over-capacitated rather than quality-limited. Reducing gated expansion_factor from 16 to 8 at K=32 may preserve most of the newly won quality while improving cost signals and possibly sharpening feature competition enough to strengthen the Pareto tradeoff."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:643:{"event_id": "evt_1774097853464698965", "ts": 1774097853, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 45, "session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The lower-LR gated sweep was a clean regression, so the next narrow exploitation move is to test the remaining untried capacity point on the best stable family. Reducing gated `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 4 at K=128 may reveal a non-dominated quality-cost tradeoff and will close the last obvious one-parameter sweep on the current anchor before returning to broader architecture work."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:734:{"event_id": "evt_1774100318480144968", "ts": 1774100318, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 51, "session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d1063-2295-7e80-8596-03d10ee10dc8", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "Stability has returned on the gated path, and the K=64 point was reconfirmed exactly in both proxy and full. The next least-risk informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost gated Pareto point at K=32 under the same strongest regime, keeping architecture, optimizer, LR, AUXK, and expansion fixed so only K changes."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:883:{"event_id": "evt_1774102784779775800", "ts": 1774102784, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 60, "session_id": "019d10a7-9492-7022-ba67-3f643cf52b9e", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d10a7-9492-7022-ba67-3f643cf52b9e", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "Stability has been restored on the gated path, and the `AUXK_ALPHA=0` K=128 run essentially matched the prior best full result, so the safest informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost Pareto point under the same newly revalidated regime. Changing only K from 128 to 64 tests whether the aux-free gated recipe can strengthen the lower-K frontier without reopening unstable architecture paths."}}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/timeline.jsonl:952:{"event_id": "evt_1774103872790403965", "ts": 1774103872, "event": "agent_action_received", "round": 64, "session_id": "019d10cb-d8a1-77a0-af5e-bbb2ae2149da", "tier": "proxy", "run_name": null, "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "status": null, "decision": null, "payload": {"session_id": "019d10cb-d8a1-77a0-af5e-bbb2ae2149da", "tier": "proxy", "family_name": "gated", "family_stage": "stabilize", "change_type": "param_only", "expected_win": "explore_unknown", "hypothesis": "The standard gated hyperparameter sweeps at K=128 are exhausted and the recent `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` recovery check regressed, so the cleanest exploitation move is to reuse the best validated aux-free gated regime and probe the remaining adjacent lower-K point. Changing only K from the strongest K=128 anchor to K=32 tests whether the recovered gated recipe can strengthen the low-cost frontier without reopening blocked architecture paths."}}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0143.json:19:    "hypothesis": "`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` stayed on a smooth enough degradation path when moving from `K=24` to `K=16` (`FVU 0.0889 -> 0.1015`), so the highest-value single-variable probe is to continue the same descent to `K=8`. Even with a further FVU increase, a credible `K=8, EF=16` point could extend the Pareto frontier toward materially lower online cost.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0012.json:19:    "hypothesis": "At the ultra-low-K anchor, increasing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from the baseline to `0.03125` for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=1, EF=12` may improve feature usage enough to reduce FVU without changing sparsity cost, potentially strengthening the frontier endpoint.",
